<eesti>1. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 1 </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;lds&auml;tted </eesti>
<inglise>General Provisions </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 1. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 1. </inglise>
<eesti>Seaduse reguleerimisala </eesti>
<inglise>Scope of application of Act </inglise>
<eesti>(1) K&auml;esolevas seaduses s&auml;testatakse Eesti laevakinnistusraamatusse v&otilde;i laevapereta prahitud laevade registrisse kantud laevadel (edaspidi Eestis registreeritud laevad) t&ouml;&ouml;tavate isikute t&ouml;&ouml;suhtega seonduvad erisused. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) This Act provides the specifications relating to employment relationships of persons working on ships entered in the Estonian ship register or the register of bareboat chartered ships (hereinafter ships registered in Estonia). </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esolevat seadust kohaldatakse &sect; 3 l&otilde;ikes 1 s&auml;testatud laevapere liikmele. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) This Act applies to crew members provided for in subsection 3 (1). </inglise>
<eesti>Muu isiku t&ouml;&ouml;suhtele kohaldatakse k&auml;esolevat seadust seadusega etten&auml;htud juhtudel. </eesti>
<inglise>This Act applies to employment relationships of other persons only in the cases prescribed by law. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 2. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 2. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;seaduste kohaldamise erisused </eesti>
<inglise>Specifications of application of labour laws </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;suhet reguleerivaid seadusi kohaldatakse k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 1 l&otilde;ikes 2 nimetatud isikutele k&auml;esolevas seaduses s&auml;testatud erisustega. </eesti>
<inglise>Acts which regulate employment relationships apply to persons specified in subsection 1 (2) of this Act together with the specifications provided for in this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 3. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 3. </inglise>
<eesti>Laevapere liige </eesti>
<inglise>Crew members </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Laevapere liikmeks k&auml;esoleva seaduse t&auml;henduses on iga laeval t&ouml;&ouml;tav isik, kellega on s&otilde;lmitud meret&ouml;&ouml;leping. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) For the purposes of this Act, every person employed on a ship with whom a seafarer's contract of employment has been concluded is a crew member. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Laev mehitatakse meres&otilde;iduohutuse seadusega (RT I 1998, 2, 47; 1999, 95, 843; 2000, 29, 171) kehtestatud korras laeva k&auml;itamiseks ja ohutuks kasutamiseks vajalike t&ouml;&ouml;tajatega ning vajaduse korral abit&ouml;&ouml;deks ja teenuste osutamiseks teiste t&ouml;&ouml;tajatega, kelle ettevalmistus peab vastama nende t&ouml;&ouml;&uuml;lesannetele. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Ships shall be manned, pursuant to the procedure established by the Maritime Safety Act (RT I 1998, 2, 47; 1999, 95, 843; 2000, 29, 171), with the necessary workers for the operation and safe use of the ship and, if necessary for the performance of auxiliary duties and the provision of services, with other workers who have completed training appropriate for their duties. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Laevapere liikmed kantakse munsterrolli, mille vormi kehtestab Vabariigi Valitsus. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Crew members shall be entered in a crew list the format of which is established by the Government of the Republic. </inglise>
<eesti>(12.12.2001 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2003 - RT I 2002, 1, 1) </eesti>
<inglise>(12.12.2001 entered into force 01.01.2003 - RT I 2002, 1, 1) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 4. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 4. </inglise>
<eesti>Reeder </eesti>
<inglise>Shipowner </inglise>
<eesti>Reeder k&auml;esoleva seaduse t&auml;henduses on ettev&otilde;tja, kes valdab laeva ja kasutab seda enda nimel ja arvel oma majandustegevuses ja s&otilde;lmib laevapere liikmega meret&ouml;&ouml;lepingu. </eesti>
<inglise>For the purposes of this Act, a shipowner is an undertaking which possesses a ship and uses the ship in economic activities in its own name and on its behalf and which concludes seafarers' contracts of employment with crew members. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 5. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 5. </inglise>
<eesti>Laeva s&otilde;idupiirkonnad </eesti>
<inglise>Navigation areas of ship </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Laeva s&otilde;idupiirkonnad k&auml;esoleva seaduse t&auml;henduses on kohaliku rannas&otilde;idu, l&auml;his&otilde;idu- ja rahvusvahelise meres&otilde;idu piirkond. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) For the purposes of this Act, the navigation areas of a ship are the areas of coastal shipping, short sea shipping and international shipping. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kohalik rannas&otilde;it on meres&otilde;it Eesti rannikul&auml;hedastes vetes kaugenemisega kaldast kuni 20 miili. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Coastal shipping means shipping in Estonian coastal waters without proceeding further than 20 miles from the shore. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) L&auml;his&otilde;it on meres&otilde;it L&auml;&auml;nemerel sisenemiseta Kieli kanalisse ja Kattegati v&auml;inas Skageni neeme paralleelist l&otilde;una poole j&auml;&auml;des. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Short sea shipping means shipping in the Baltic Sea without entering the Kiel Canal and in the Kattegat Strait to the south of the parallel of Cape Skagen. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Rahvusvaheline meres&otilde;it on meres&otilde;it v&auml;ljaspool kohaliku rannas&otilde;idu piirkonda, mille ajal peatutakse v&auml;lisriigi sadamas. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) International shipping means shipping outside the area of coastal shipping during which the vessel stops in a foreign port. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 6. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 6. </inglise>
<eesti>Seaduse imperatiivsus </eesti>
<inglise>Imperative nature of Act </inglise>
<eesti>K&auml;esolevas seaduses s&auml;testatust k&otilde;rvalekalduvad kokkulepped laevapere liikme v&otilde;i muu laeval t&ouml;&ouml;tava isiku kahjuks on t&uuml;hised, kui seadusega ei ole ette n&auml;htud teisiti. </eesti>
<inglise>Agreements derogating from the provisions of this Act which damage the interests of a crew member or any other person employed on a ship are void, unless otherwise prescribed by law. </inglise>
<eesti>2. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 2 </inglise>
<eesti>Meret&ouml;&ouml;leping </eesti>
<inglise>Seafarer's Contract of Employment </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 7. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 7. </inglise>
<eesti>Meret&ouml;&ouml;lepingu pooled </eesti>
<inglise>Parties to seafarer's contract of employment </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Meret&ouml;&ouml;lepingu pooled on laevapere liige, kes on v&auml;hemalt 18-aastane, ja reeder v&otilde;i muu t&ouml;&ouml;andja. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The parties to a seafarer's contract of employment are a crew member who is at least 18 years of age and a shipowner or another employer. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Erandina v&otilde;ib meret&ouml;&ouml;lepingu s&otilde;lmida reederi loal kapten, kui see on tingitud ohutu meres&otilde;idu j&auml;tkamise vajadusest. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) As an exception and if it is necessary in order to continue safe shipping, a seafarer's contract of employment may be concluded by the master with the permission of the shipowner. </inglise>
<eesti>Meret&ouml;&ouml;lepingu s&otilde;lmimise vajadusest tuleb v&otilde;imaluse korral reederile eelnevalt teatada. </eesti>
<inglise>If possible, the shipowner shall be notified of the need to conclude a seafarer's contract of employment in advance. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 2 nimetatud juhul v&otilde;ib meret&ouml;&ouml;lepingu s&otilde;lmida kuni neljaks kuuks. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) In the case specified in subsection (2) of this section, a seafarer's contract of employment may be entered into for a term of up to four months. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) K&auml;esolevas paragrahvis s&auml;testatud n&otilde;uete rikkumine ei too kaasa meret&ouml;&ouml;lepingu t&uuml;hisust. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Non-compliance with the requirements provided for in this section shall not render a seafarer's contract of employment void. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 8. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 8. </inglise>
<eesti>Meret&ouml;&ouml;lepingu m&otilde;iste, tingimused ja vorm </eesti>
<inglise>Definition, terms and format of seafarer's contract of employment </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Meret&ouml;&ouml;leping on reederi v&otilde;i muu t&ouml;&ouml;andja ja laevapere liikme vaheline kokkulepe, mille kohaselt laevapere liige kohustub t&ouml;&ouml;tama reederi huvides, alludes tema juhtimisele ja kontrollimisele, reeder aga kohustub maksma laevapere liikmele t&ouml;&ouml; eest tasu ning tagama talle seaduse, muu &otilde;igusakti, meret&ouml;&ouml;- ja kollektiivlepinguga ning poolte kokkuleppel etten&auml;htud t&ouml;&ouml;tingimused. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A seafarer's contract of employment is an agreement between a shipowner or another employer and a crew member under which the crew member undertakes to work in the interests of the shipowner in subordination to the management and supervision of the shipowner and the shipowner undertakes to remunerate the crew member for such work and to provide the crew member with such working conditions as are prescribed by law, other legislation, the seafarer's contract of employment or a collective agreement and by agreement between the parties. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Meret&ouml;&ouml;leping s&otilde;lmitakse kirjalikult kahes eksemplaris, millest &uuml;ks j&auml;&auml;b reederile, teine laevapere liikmele. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A seafarer's contract of employment is entered into in writing in two original copies, one of which shall be retained by the shipowner and the other by the crew member. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Meret&ouml;&ouml;lepingus peavad sisalduma v&auml;hemalt j&auml;rgmised andmed: </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A seafarer's contract of employment shall contain at least the following information: </inglise>
<eesti>1) meret&ouml;&ouml;lepingu pooled, sealhulgas laevapere liikme isikuandmed ja isikukood; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the parties to the seafarer's employment contract, including personal data and the personal identification code of the crew member; </inglise>
<eesti>2) meret&ouml;&ouml;lepingu s&otilde;lmimise aeg ja koht; </eesti>
<inglise>2) the time and place of entry into the seafarer's contract of employment; </inglise>
<eesti>3) t&ouml;&ouml;le asumise aeg ja koht; </eesti>
<inglise>3) the date and place of commencement of employment; </inglise>
<eesti>4) m&auml;&auml;ratud ajaks s&otilde;lmitud meret&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;ppemise t&auml;htaeg; </eesti>
<inglise>4) the date of expiry of the term of the seafarer's contract if the contract is entered into for a specified period of time; </inglise>
<eesti>5) esimene laev, millel laevapere liige t&ouml;&ouml;le asub; </eesti>
<inglise>5) the first vessel on which the crew member is to commence employment; </inglise>
<eesti>6) amet ja t&ouml;&ouml; kirjeldus v&otilde;i viide ametijuhendile; </eesti>
<inglise>6) the position and a description of the duties or reference to the job description; </inglise>
<eesti>7) t&ouml;&ouml;tasu, t&ouml;&ouml;tasu maksmise viis ja aeg; </eesti>
<inglise>7) wages, and the time and method of payment thereof; </inglise>
<eesti>8) t&ouml;&ouml;aeg; </eesti>
<inglise>8) working time; </inglise>
<eesti>9) laevapere liikme iga-aastase puhkuse kestus; </eesti>
<inglise>9) the length of the annual holiday of the crew member; </inglise>
<eesti>10) meret&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamisest etteteatamise t&auml;htajad; </eesti>
<inglise>10) the terms for giving advance notice of termination of the seafarer's contract of employment; </inglise>
<eesti>11) poolte allkirjad. </eesti>
<inglise>11) the signatures of the parties. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) K&auml;esolevas paragrahvis nimetatud vormin&otilde;uete eiramine ei too kaasa lepingu t&uuml;hisust. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Non-compliance with the formal requirements provided for in this section shall not render a seafarer's contract of employment void. </inglise>
<eesti>Laevapere liige v&otilde;ib n&otilde;uda meret&ouml;&ouml;lepingu vormistamist vastavalt k&auml;esolevas paragrahvis s&auml;testatule. </eesti>
<inglise>A crew member may request that his or her seafarer's contract of employment be prepared pursuant to the provisions of this section. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 9. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 9. </inglise>
<eesti>Meret&ouml;&ouml;lepingu t&auml;htaeg </eesti>
<inglise>Term of seafarer's contract of employment </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Meret&ouml;&ouml;leping s&otilde;lmitakse: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A seafarer's contract of employment is entered into: </inglise>
<eesti>1) m&auml;&auml;ramata ajaks; </eesti>
<inglise>1) for an unspecified term; </inglise>
<eesti>2) m&auml;&auml;ratud ajaks, kuid mitte kauemaks kui viieks aastaks. </eesti>
<inglise>2) for a specified term but not for longer than five years. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) M&auml;&auml;ratud ajaks v&otilde;ib meret&ouml;&ouml;lepingu s&otilde;lmida: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A seafarer's contract of employment may be entered into for a specified term: </inglise>
<eesti>1) kindlaksm&auml;&auml;ratud reisiks v&otilde;i reisideks; </eesti>
<inglise>1) for a particular voyage or particular voyages; </inglise>
<eesti>2) teatud t&ouml;&ouml; tegemise ajaks; </eesti>
<inglise>2) for the completion of a specific task; </inglise>
<eesti>3) ajutiselt &auml;raoleva laevapere liikme asendamiseks; </eesti>
<inglise>3) for the replacement of a crew member who is temporarily absent; </inglise>
<eesti>4) t&ouml;&ouml;de mahu ajutise suurenemise korral; </eesti>
<inglise>4) in the event of a temporary increase in the volume of work; </inglise>
<eesti>5) meret&ouml;&ouml;lepingus laevapere liikmele erisoodustuste etten&auml;gemise korral; </eesti>
<inglise>5) if special benefits are prescribed for the crew member in his or her seafarer's contract of employment; </inglise>
<eesti>6) navigatsiooniperioodiks. </eesti>
<inglise>6) for a navigational period. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 10. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 10. </inglise>
<eesti>Meret&ouml;&ouml;lepingu s&otilde;lmimiseks n&otilde;utavad dokumendid </eesti>
<inglise>Documents required for entry into seafarer's contract of employment </inglise>
<eesti>Reeder v&otilde;i muu t&ouml;&ouml;andja v&otilde;ib meret&ouml;&ouml;lepingu s&otilde;lmimiseks laevapere liikmelt n&otilde;uda j&auml;rgmisi dokumente: </eesti>
<inglise>A shipowner or other employer may require the following documents from a crew member for entry into a seafarer's contract of employment: </inglise>
<eesti>1) isikut t&otilde;endav dokument; </eesti>
<inglise>1) an identity document; </inglise>
<eesti>2) t&ouml;&ouml;raamat; </eesti>
<inglise>2) an employment record book; </inglise>
<eesti>3) teenistusraamat v&otilde;i meres&otilde;idutunnistus; </eesti>
<inglise>3) a discharge book or a certificate of record of service on Estonian ships; </inglise>
<eesti>4) meres&otilde;idudiplom v&otilde;i kutsetunnistus n&otilde;utava kvalifikatsiooni ja hariduse kohta; </eesti>
<inglise>4) a seafarer's certificate certifying the required qualifications and education; </inglise>
<eesti>5) terviset&otilde;end; </eesti>
<inglise>5) a health certificate; </inglise>
<eesti>6) v&auml;lismaalase puhul elamis- v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;luba; </eesti>
<inglise>6) in the case of an alien, a residence permit or work permit; </inglise>
<eesti>7) muud Veeteede Ameti poolt n&otilde;utavad kvalifikatsiooni t&otilde;endavad dokumendid. </eesti>
<inglise>7) other documents certifying qualifications, as required by the Maritime Administration. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 11. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 11. </inglise>
<eesti>Kohales&otilde;idukulud meret&ouml;&ouml;lepingu s&otilde;lmimisel </eesti>
<inglise>Travelling expenses upon entry into seafarer's contract of employment </inglise>
<eesti>Kui laevapere liige peab t&ouml;&ouml;le asuma laeval, mis ei asu meret&ouml;&ouml;lepingu s&otilde;lmimise kohas, peab reeder korraldama oma kulul laevapere liikme s&otilde;idu laeva asukohta ning tagama talle toidu ja majutuse kohales&otilde;idu ajal. </eesti>
<inglise>If a crew member has to commence employment on a ship which is located elsewhere than the place where the seafarer's contract of employment is entered into, the shipowner shall, at the shipowner's expense, make travel arrangements for the crew member to reach the location of the ship and provide the crew member with food and accommodation during the journey. </inglise>
<eesti>3. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 3 </inglise>
<eesti>Laevapere liikme &otilde;igused, kohustused ja vastutus </eesti>
<inglise>Rights, Duties and Liability of Crew Members </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 12. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 12. </inglise>
<eesti>Laevapere liikme kohustused </eesti>
<inglise>Duties of crew members </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Laevapere liige on kohustatud: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A crew member is required to: </inglise>
<eesti>1) tegema meret&ouml;&ouml;lepingus ja ametijuhendis etten&auml;htud t&ouml;&ouml;d; </eesti>
<inglise>1) perform the work specified in his or her seafarer's contract of employment and job description; </inglise>
<eesti>2) osalema p&auml;&auml;ste- ja tulet&otilde;rjeharjutustes; </eesti>
<inglise>2) participate in lifeboat and fire-fighting drills; </inglise>
<eesti>3) t&auml;itma ilma erikorralduseta &uuml;lesandeid, mis tulenevad t&ouml;&ouml; iseloomust v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml; &uuml;ldisest k&auml;igust; </eesti>
<inglise>3) perform, without special orders, tasks which arise from the character of his or her work or during the general course of his or her work; </inglise>
<eesti>4) hoidma laeva ja sellel olevat vara; </eesti>
<inglise>4) maintain the vessel and property thereon; </inglise>
<eesti>5) kandma t&ouml;&ouml;ajal reederi m&auml;&auml;ratud t&ouml;&ouml;- ja eririietust. </eesti>
<inglise>5) wear working clothes and special clothing prescribed by the shipowner during working time. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Laevapere liige peab t&auml;itma &otilde;igeaegselt ja t&auml;pselt kapteni v&otilde;i muu p&auml;deva isiku seaduslikke korraldusi. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A crew member shall carry out lawful orders from the master or other competent persons in a timely and accurate manner. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Laevapere liige peab t&auml;itma t&ouml;&ouml;&uuml;lesandeid meret&ouml;&ouml;lepingus etten&auml;htud mahus ning j&auml;rgima kehtestatud sisekorraeeskirju ja t&ouml;&ouml;aega. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A crew member shall perform his or her duties to the extent prescribed by his or her seafarer's contract of employment and observe the established internal procedure rules and working time. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 13. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 13. </inglise>
<eesti>Laeva ohutusega seotud korralduste t&auml;itmine </eesti>
<inglise>Carrying out orders related to safety of ship </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Lisaks k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 12 nimetatule on laevapere liige kohustatud j&auml;rgima kapteni v&otilde;i muu p&auml;deva isiku korraldusi, mis on vajalikud: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) In addition to the provisions of &sect; 12 of this Act, a crew member is required to observe orders from the master or other competent persons which are necessary: </inglise>
<eesti>1) laeval olevaid v&otilde;i teisi isikuid &auml;hvardava ohu v&auml;ltimiseks; </eesti>
<inglise>1) to avoid danger to persons on board the ship or to other persons; </inglise>
<eesti>2) laeva ohutuse tagamiseks; </eesti>
<inglise>2) to ensure the safety of the ship; </inglise>
<eesti>3) lasti riknemise v&otilde;i h&auml;vimise v&auml;ltimiseks; </eesti>
<inglise>3) to prevent the loss of or damage to the cargo; </inglise>
<eesti>4) teisi laevu &auml;hvardava ohu v&auml;ltimiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>4) to avoid danger to other ships. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Laevahuku korral on laevapere liige kohustatud osalema laeval olevate isikute ja laeva lasti p&auml;&auml;stmisel. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) In the event of a shipwreck, a crew member is required to participate in rescuing the persons on board the ship and salvaging the cargo of the ship. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 14. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 14. </inglise>
<eesti>K&auml;itumine laeval </eesti>
<inglise>Conduct on ship </inglise>
<eesti>Laevapere liikmed k&auml;ituvad &uuml;ksteise suhtes usalduslikult ja vajaliku viisakusega, edendavad koost&ouml;&ouml;d ning tagavad laeval korra ja ohutuse. </eesti>
<inglise>Crew members shall behave toward each other in a spirit of trust and with the necessary politeness, and shall co-operate and ensure order and safety on board. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 15. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 15. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml; tegemise koht </eesti>
<inglise>Place of work </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kui meret&ouml;&ouml;lepingus ei ole kokku lepitud teisiti, on laevapere liige kohustatud t&ouml;&ouml;tama &uuml;ksnes lepingus m&auml;rgitud laeval. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Unless otherwise agreed in the seafarer's contract of employment, a crew member is required to work only on the ship indicated in the contract. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Laeva juhtkonda kuuluva isiku v&otilde;ib reeder oma ettev&otilde;tte piires &uuml;mber paigutada teisele laevale, s&auml;ilitades talle v&auml;hemalt senised meret&ouml;&ouml;lepinguga m&auml;&auml;ratud t&ouml;&ouml;tingimused, kui &uuml;mberpaigutamine on ettev&otilde;tte t&ouml;&ouml;korraldust arvestades vajalik ja meret&ouml;&ouml;lepingus ei ole kokku lepitud teisiti. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A shipowner may transfer a person who is one of a ship's officers to another ship within the shipowner's enterprise provided that at least the same working conditions as those prescribed by his or her seafarer's contract of employment will be maintained for him or her if the transfer is necessary considering the organisation of the work of the enterprise, unless otherwise agreed in the seafarer's contract of employment. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 16. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 16. </inglise>
<eesti>Laevaloleku kohustus laeva &auml;hvardava ohu korral </eesti>
<inglise>Obligation to remain on board in event of danger to ship </inglise>
<eesti>&Auml;hvardava laevahuku v&otilde;i muu laeval olevaid isikuid &auml;hvardava otsese ohu korral ei lahku laevapere liige laevalt ilma kapteni v&otilde;i teda asendava isiku loata. </eesti>
<inglise>If the ship is in danger of being shipwrecked or in the event of any other direct danger to persons on board the ship, crew members shall not leave the ship without the permission of the master or the person substituting for the master. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 17. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 17. </inglise>
<eesti>Maalemineku&otilde;igus </eesti>
<inglise>Right to go ashore </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Laevapere liikmel on laeva sadamas v&otilde;i reidil seismise ajal &otilde;igus v&auml;ljaspool oma t&ouml;&ouml;aega kapteni v&otilde;i teda asendava isiku loal maale minna. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A crew member has the right to go ashore, with the permission of the master or the person substituting for the master, outside of his or her working time while the ship is in port or at a roadstead. </inglise>
<eesti>Loa andmisest v&otilde;ib keelduda, kui kapteni v&otilde;i teda asendava isiku arvates on laevapere liikme laevale j&auml;&auml;mine vajalik laeva, laeval oleva isiku v&otilde;i lasti ohutuse tagamiseks v&otilde;i laeva eelseisva v&auml;ljumisega seotud t&ouml;&ouml;kohustuste t&auml;itmiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>Permission may be refused if, in the opinion of the master or the person substituting for the master, it is necessary for the crew member to remain on board the ship to ensure the safety of the ship, persons on board the ship or the cargo or to perform duties related to the impending departure of the ship. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Vajaduse korral peab kapten korraldama laevapere liikmete maalemineku viisil, mis ei takista t&ouml;&ouml;d laeval ega ole seotud ebam&otilde;istlike kulutustega. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Where necessary, the master shall organise the going ashore of crew members in a manner which does not obstruct work on the ship and does not involve unreasonable costs. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 18. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 18. </inglise>
<eesti>Laevapere liikme &otilde;igus lahkuda laevalt </eesti>
<inglise>Right of crew member to leave ship </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Laevapere liige v&otilde;ib lahkuda laevalt ja n&otilde;uda reederilt t&ouml;&ouml;koha muutmist, kui: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A crew member may leave the ship and request that the shipowner transfer him or her to another place of work if: </inglise>
<eesti>1) laev, millel laevapere liige on kohustatud t&ouml;&ouml;tama, ei ole merek&otilde;lblik ja kapten ei t&auml;ida oma kohustust kontrollida laeva merek&otilde;lblikkust vastavalt k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 33 s&auml;testatule ning kavatseb v&auml;ljuda sadamast; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the ship on which the crew member is required to work is not seaworthy and if the master fails to perform his or her duty to verify the seaworthiness of the ship pursuant to the provisions of &sect; 33 of this Act and intends to leave port; </inglise>
<eesti>2) laevapere elamistingimused laeval ohustavad laevapere liikme elu v&otilde;i tervist ning reeder ei rakenda olukorra parandamiseks vajalikke abin&otilde;usid; </eesti>
<inglise>2) the living conditions of the crew on the ship endanger the life or health of the crew member and the shipowner fails to apply measures necessary to improve the situation; </inglise>
<eesti>3) laevapere liiget on laeval v&auml;&auml;rkoheldud ja kaptenil ei ole &otilde;nnestunud pakkuda talle kaitset, kuigi kaptenile on vastavatest asjaoludest teatatud; </eesti>
<inglise>3) the crew member has been subjected to abuse on the ship and the master has been unable to provide him or her with protection although the master has been notified of the relevant facts; </inglise>
<eesti>4) laev kaotab &otilde;iguse s&otilde;ita Eesti lipu all; </eesti>
<inglise>4) the ship loses the right to fly the Estonian flag; </inglise>
<eesti>5) meret&ouml;&ouml;leping on s&otilde;lmitud kindlaksm&auml;&auml;ratud reisiks ja laeva s&otilde;idu sihtkohta muudetakse; </eesti>
<inglise>5) his or her seafarer's contract of employment has been entered into for a particular voyage and the destination of the ship is changed; </inglise>
<eesti>6) p&auml;rast t&ouml;&ouml; alustamist laeval selgub, et laev v&otilde;ib sattuda v&otilde;&otilde;rv&otilde;imu kontrolli alla v&otilde;i saada vigastada s&otilde;japiirkonnas v&otilde;i et nimetatud oht on m&auml;rgatavalt suurenenud; </eesti>
<inglise>6) after commencement of employment on the ship it becomes evident that the ship may be subjected to the authority of a foreign power or be damaged in a war zone, or that the danger thereof has increased significantly; </inglise>
<eesti>7) p&auml;rast t&ouml;&ouml; alustamist laeval selgub, et sadam, kuhu on kavas suunduda, on kuulutatud epideemiapiirkonnaks. </eesti>
<inglise>7) after commencement of employment on the ship it becomes evident that the port of destination has been declared to be an area suffering from an epidemic. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 s&auml;testatud juhtudel on laevapere liikmel &otilde;igus laevalt lahkuda enne s&otilde;idu algust v&otilde;i esimeses sadamas, kus laev sildub p&auml;rast nimetatud asjaoludest teadasaamist. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) In the cases provided for in subsection (1) of this section, a crew member has the right to leave the ship before the commencement of the voyage or at the first port where the ship is moored after becoming aware of the said circumstances. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kui laevapere liige k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 s&auml;testatud juhtudel lahkub laevalt, on reeder kohustatud korraldama oma kulul laevapere liikme kojus&otilde;idu vastavalt k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 57 s&auml;testatule v&otilde;i paigutama laevapere liikme t&ouml;&ouml;le muule laevale oma ettev&otilde;ttes. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) If a crew member leaves the ship in the cases provided for in subsection (1) of this section, the shipowner shall organise, at the shipowner's expense, the repatriation of the crew member pursuant to the provisions of &sect; 57 of this Act or post the crew member to work on another ship in the shipowner's enterprise. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui laevapere liige asub t&ouml;&ouml;le muul laeval, h&uuml;vitab reeder laevapere liikmele laeva vahetamisega seotud kulud. </eesti>
<inglise>If the crew member commences work on another ship, the shipowner shall reimburse the crew member for expenses related to the change of ship. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 19. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 19. </inglise>
<eesti>Laevapere liikme vastutus reederile tekitatud kahju eest </eesti>
<inglise>Liability of crew members for damage caused to shipowner </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Laevapere liige vastutab meret&ouml;&ouml;lepingu rikkumise korral reederile s&uuml;&uuml;liselt tekitatud kahju eest. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A crew member is liable for damage wrongfully caused to the shipowner in the event of a violation of his or her seafarer's contract of employment. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Laevapere liige, kes t&ouml;&ouml;&uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmisel on kerge hooletusega tekitanud reederile kahju, vastutab reederile tekitatud kahju eest kuni oma keskmise kuupalga ulatuses. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A crew member who causes damage to the shipowner due to slight negligence in the course of performing his or her duties is liable for the damage caused to the shipowner to the extent of his or her average monthly wages. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Laevapere liige, kes t&ouml;&ouml;&uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmisel on raske hooletusega tekitanud reederile kahju, vastutab reederile tekitatud kahju eest kuni oma kaheteistk&uuml;mne keskmise kuupalga ulatuses. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A crew member who causes damage to the shipowner due to gross negligence in the course of performing his or her duties is liable for the damage caused to the shipowner to the extent of twelve times his or her average monthly wages. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Kui laevapere liige on t&ouml;&ouml;&uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmisel tekitanud reederile tahtlikult kahju, on ta kohustatud h&uuml;vitama reederile tekitatud kahju t&auml;ies ulatuses. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) If a crew member intentionally causes damage to the shipowner in the course of performing his or her duties, the crew member shall compensate for the damage caused to the shipowner in full. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Laevapere liikme s&uuml;&uuml; t&otilde;endamise kohustus lasub reederil. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) The burden of proof of the fault of the crew member lies with the shipowner. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui kahju tekkimises on s&uuml;&uuml;di nii reeder kui ka laevapere liige, vastutavad nad proportsionaalselt oma s&uuml;&uuml; astmele. </eesti>
<inglise>If both the shipowner and the crew member are at fault for causing damage, they shall be liable in proportion to the degree of their fault. </inglise>
<eesti>4. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 4 </inglise>
<eesti>Reederi ja kapteni kohustused ja vastutus </eesti>
<inglise>Duties and Liability of Shipowners and Masters </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 20. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 20. </inglise>
<eesti>Reederi kohustused </eesti>
<inglise>Duties of shipowners </inglise>
<eesti>Reeder on kohustatud: </eesti>
<inglise>A shipowner is required to: </inglise>
<eesti>1) tagama kaptenile vajalike vahendite olemasolu seadusega etten&auml;htud kohustuste t&auml;itmiseks; </eesti>
<inglise>1) provide the master with the resources necessary to perform the duties prescribed by law; </inglise>
<eesti>2) tagama laevapere liikmele kokkulepitud t&ouml;&ouml; ning andma selgelt ja &otilde;igeaegselt vajalikke korraldusi; </eesti>
<inglise>2) provide crew members with the agreed work and give the necessary orders clearly and in a timely manner; </inglise>
<eesti>3) maksma t&ouml;&ouml; eest tasu meret&ouml;&ouml;lepinguga kindlaksm&auml;&auml;ratud tingimustel ja ajal; </eesti>
<inglise>3) pay wages for work under the conditions and at the time determined in the seafarer's contract of employment; </inglise>
<eesti>4) tagama laeval ohutud t&ouml;&ouml;- ja elamistingimused; </eesti>
<inglise>4) ensure safe working and living conditions on the ship; </inglise>
<eesti>5) tutvustama t&ouml;&ouml;lev&otilde;tmisel ja t&ouml;&ouml;tamise ajal laevapere liikmetele sisekorra-, t&ouml;&ouml;ohutus-, t&ouml;&ouml;tervishoiu-, keskkonna- ja tuleohutusn&otilde;udeid laeval ning t&ouml;&ouml;keskkonna ohtlike ja kahjulike m&otilde;jurite taset t&ouml;&ouml;- ja olmeruumides; </eesti>
<inglise>5) familiarise crew members, upon their hiring and during their employment, with the internal procedures and with the occupational health and safety, environmental and fire safety requirements on the ship and with the levels of dangerous and harmful factors in workrooms and non-work rooms resulting from the working environment; </inglise>
<eesti>6) andma etten&auml;htud puhkust ja maksma puhkusetasu; </eesti>
<inglise>6) grant holidays as prescribed and pay holiday pay; </inglise>
<eesti>7) tagama t&ouml;&ouml;- ja puhkeaja re&zcaron;iimi; </eesti>
<inglise>7) ensure a working and rest time regime; </inglise>
<eesti>8) t&auml;itma teisi seaduse, muu &otilde;igusakti ning kollektiivlepinguga etten&auml;htud kohustusi. </eesti>
<inglise>8) perform other duties prescribed by law, other legislation or a collective agreement. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 21. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 21. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;tasu arvestamise kohustuse tekkimise aeg </eesti>
<inglise>Time when obligation to calculate wages arises </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&ouml;&ouml;tasu arvestamise kohustus tekib alates laevapere liikme t&ouml;&ouml;le asumise p&auml;evast. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The obligation to calculate wages arises as of the date on which the crew member commences employment. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui laev, millel laevapere liige peab t&ouml;&ouml;le asuma, asub v&auml;lisriigis ja meret&ouml;&ouml;lepingu s&otilde;lmimine ei toimu laeva asukohas, tekib t&ouml;&ouml;tasu arvestamise kohustus laevale kohales&otilde;idu alustamise hetkest, kui meret&ouml;&ouml;lepingus ei ole kokku lepitud teisiti. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If the ship on which a crew member is to commence work is located in a foreign country and the seafarer's contract of employment is not concluded at the location of the ship, the obligation to calculate wages arises as of the moment at which the crew member commences his or her journey to the ship, unless otherwise agreed in the seafarer's contract of employment. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 22. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 22. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;tasu maksmise aja ja viisiga seonduvad erisused </eesti>
<inglise>Specifications relating to time and method of payment of wages </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&ouml;&ouml;tasu makstakse laevapere liikmele iga kuu l&otilde;pus, kui t&ouml;&ouml;tasu maksmiseks ei ole kokku lepitud l&uuml;hemat t&auml;htaega v&otilde;i muud t&auml;htp&auml;eva v&otilde;i kui muu t&auml;htp&auml;ev ei ole m&auml;&auml;ratud seaduse, meret&ouml;&ouml;- v&otilde;i kollektiivlepinguga. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Wages shall be paid to crew members at the end of each month unless a shorter term or another due date is agreed for the payment of wages or another due date is determined by law, a seafarer's contract of employment or a collective agreement. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;tasu maksmist sularahas v&otilde;ib laevapere liige n&otilde;uda &uuml;ksnes laeva sadamas v&otilde;i reidil seismise ajal. </eesti>
<inglise>A crew member may only request that his or her wages be paid in cash while the ship is in a port or at a roadstead. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Laevapere liikme avalduse alusel kantakse t&ouml;&ouml;tasu &uuml;le laevapere liikme m&auml;&auml;ratud pangaarvele. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) At the request of the crew member, his or her wages shall be transferred to a bank account designated by him or her. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Laevapere liikme n&otilde;usolekul v&otilde;ib t&ouml;&ouml;tasu maksta riigi valuutas, mille territoriaalvetes laev t&ouml;&ouml;tasun&otilde;ude tekkimise ajal asub, v&otilde;i muus vabalt konverteeritavas valuutas. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) With the consent of the crew member, wages may be paid in the currency of the country in whose territorial waters the ship is located when the claim for payment of wages arises or in any other freely convertible currency. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) T&ouml;&ouml;tasu maksmisega seotud kulud kannab reeder. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Costs relating to the payment of wages shall be borne by the shipowner. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Kui laevapere liikmete arv etten&auml;gematu s&uuml;ndmuse t&otilde;ttu reisi kestel v&auml;heneb ja seet&otilde;ttu suureneb laevapere liikmete t&ouml;&ouml;koormus, makstakse neile lisatasu laevapere v&auml;henemise t&otilde;ttu reederi poolt v&auml;ljamaksmata t&ouml;&ouml;tasude arvel s&auml;&auml;stetud summa ulatuses. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) If, due to unforeseeable circumstances, the number of crew members decreases during a voyage and the work load of crew members increases as a result, crew members shall be paid additional remuneration to the extent of the amount saved by the shipowner in unpaid wages due to the decrease in the crew. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 23. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 23. </inglise>
<eesti>Teadetetahvel laeva t&ouml;&ouml;korraldusega </eesti>
<inglise>Notice board with shipboard working arrangements </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Teadetetahvel laeva t&ouml;&ouml;korraldusega paigutatakse kergesti ligip&auml;&auml;setavasse kohta ja sellel peab olema: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A notice board showing shipboard working arrangements shall be positioned in an easily accessible place and it shall contain: </inglise>
<eesti>1) iga teenistuskoha kohta v&auml;hemalt t&ouml;&ouml;tamise ajakava merel ja sadamas; </eesti>
<inglise>1) at least the schedule of service at sea and service in port for each position; </inglise>
<eesti>2) maksimaalne t&ouml;&ouml;aeg ja minimaalne puhkeaeg vastavalt seadusele, muule &otilde;igusaktile v&otilde;i kollektiivlepingule; </eesti>
<inglise>2) the maximum hours of work and the minimum hours of rest required by law, other legislation or a collective agreement; </inglise>
<eesti>3) meret&ouml;&ouml;lepingu vorm; </eesti>
<inglise>3) a form for a seafarer's contract of employment; </inglise>
<eesti>4) koopiad t&ouml;&ouml;- ja puhkeaega reguleerivatest seadustest, muudest &otilde;igusaktidest ning vastavad kollektiivlepingud. </eesti>
<inglise>4) copies of Acts and other legislation regulating working and rest time and relevant collective agreements. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud teadetetahvlil peab informatsioon olema eesti ja inglise keeles. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Information on the notice board specified in subsection (1) of this section shall be in Estonian and English. </inglise>
<eesti>Teadetetahvel koostatakse standardformaadis. </eesti>
<inglise>The notice board shall be set up in a standardised format. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 24. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 24. </inglise>
<eesti>Laevapere liikme t&ouml;&ouml;- ja eririietus </eesti>
<inglise>Working clothes and special clothing for crew members </inglise>
<eesti>Reeder tagab oma kulul laevapere liikmele t&ouml;&ouml; tegemiseks vajaliku t&ouml;&ouml;- ja eririietuse ning kaitsevahendid. </eesti>
<inglise>The shipowner shall, at the shipowner's expense, provide crew members with working clothes and special clothing and protective equipment necessary for the performance of their work. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 25. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 25. </inglise>
<eesti>Ametiriietus </eesti>
<inglise>Uniforms </inglise>
<eesti>Laeva juhtkonna liikmel on kohustus kanda ametiriietust. </eesti>
<inglise>Ship's officers are required to wear uniforms. </inglise>
<eesti>Laeva juhtkonna liikme ametiriietuse ja ametialase eraldusm&auml;rkide kirjelduse kehtestab teede- ja sideminister. </eesti>
<inglise>A description of the uniforms of ship's officers and their distinguishing marks shall be established by the Minister of Transport and Communications. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 26. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 26. </inglise>
<eesti>Toitlustamine </eesti>
<inglise>Catering </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kapten korraldab reederi kulul laevaperele toidu varumise ja laevapere liikme korrap&auml;rase toitlustamise laeval. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The master shall, at the expense of the shipowner, maintain a food supply for crew members and regularly provide food for crew members on board the ship. </inglise>
<eesti>Laevapere liikme toidunormid ja toitlustamise korra laeval kehtestab sotsiaalminister. </eesti>
<inglise>Food rations for crew members and the procedure for the provision of food on board ships shall be established by the Minister of Social Affairs. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Laevapere liikmel on keelatud toitlustamiseks &uuml;leantut v&otilde;&otilde;randamise eesm&auml;rgil laevalt v&auml;lja viia. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Crew members are prohibited from taking that which is provided for catering away from the ship for the purpose of its transfer. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kohalikku rannas&otilde;itu sooritaval laeval, kus laevapere liiget ei toitlustata, maksab reeder laevapere liikmele &auml;raj&auml;&auml;nud toitlustamise korral saamata j&auml;&auml;nud toidu eest h&uuml;vitist, mis lisatakse sama kuu t&ouml;&ouml;tasule. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) If food is not provided for crew members on a vessel engaged in coastal shipping, the shipowner shall pay the crew members a benefit for unreceived food if food is not provided and the benefit shall be added to the wages for the current month. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Reisi ajal erandlike asjaolude t&otilde;ttu tekkinud toidu- v&otilde;i joogiveevarude ebapiisavuse korral v&otilde;ib kapten toidunorme v&auml;hendada. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) In the event of a shortage of food or water supplies caused by extraordinary circumstances during the voyage, the master may reduce the food rations. </inglise>
<eesti>Nimetatud juhul h&uuml;vitatakse laevapere liikmele saamata j&auml;&auml;nud toit reederi ja laevapere liikme vahel kokkulepitud viisil. </eesti>
<inglise>In such case, unreceived food shall be compensated for to a crew member in the manner agreed upon by the shipowner and the crew member. </inglise>
<eesti>Kapten korraldab erandlike asjaolude t&otilde;ttu tekkinud toidu- v&otilde;i joogiveevarude ebapiisavuse korral laevapere toidu- ja joogiveevarude &uuml;le arvestuse pidamist logiraamatus. </eesti>
<inglise>In the case of a shortage of food or water supplies caused by extraordinary circumstances, the master shall organise the keeping of records on the food and water supply of the crew in the logbook. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;igetes 3 ja 4 nimetatud h&uuml;vitis maksustatakse samadel alustel nagu toiduratsiooni maksumuse maksustamine. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) The benefit specified in subsections (3) and (4) of this section is subject to taxation on the same bases as the cost of a food ration is subject to taxation. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 27. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 27. </inglise>
<eesti>Majutus </eesti>
<inglise>Accommodation </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Laevapere liikmel on laevaloleku ajal &otilde;igus n&otilde;uetele vastavale majutusele. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) While on board the ship, crew members are entitled to accommodation which complies with the requirements. </inglise>
<eesti>N&otilde;uded laevapere liikme laeval majutamise tingimustele kehtestab sotsiaalminister. </eesti>
<inglise>The requirements for the conditions of accommodation for crew members on board ships shall be established by the Minister of Social Affairs. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Laevapere liikmel on kohustus hoida tema kasutusse antud ruume korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Crew members are required to keep the rooms of which they are granted use in order. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 28. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 28. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;tervishoiu- ja t&ouml;&ouml;ohutusn&otilde;uded </eesti>
<inglise>Occupational health and safety requirements </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Laevapere liikmele tagatakse meditsiiniabi andmine laeval. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Crew members shall be provided with medical care on the ship. </inglise>
<eesti>Meditsiiniabi korraldamise n&otilde;uded laeval ja Eestis registreeritud laeval n&otilde;utava meditsiinivarustuse nimekirja kehtestab sotsiaalminister. </eesti>
<inglise>The requirements for the organisation of medical care on ships and the list of medical equipment required on ships registered in Estonia shall be established by the Minister of Social Affairs. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Laevapere liige l&auml;bib eelneva ja perioodilise tervisekontrolli meres&otilde;iduohutuse seaduses s&auml;testatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Crew members shall undergo a prior medical examination and routine medical examinations pursuant to the procedure provided for in the Maritime Safety Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Reederi v&otilde;i kapteni n&otilde;udmisel l&auml;bib laevapere liige ennet&auml;htaegse tervisekontrolli, kui on p&otilde;hjendatud kahtlusi laevapere liikme tervisliku seisundi mittevastavuse suhtes t&ouml;&ouml;ks laeval. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A crew member shall, at the request of the shipowner or master, undergo a medical examination before the prescribed time if there is reasonable doubt as to whether the state of health of the crew member is suitable for working on the ship. </inglise>
<eesti>4. </eesti>
<inglise>4. </inglise>
<eesti>K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;igetes 2 ja 3 nimetatud tervisekontrolli kulud kannab reeder, v&auml;lja arvatud meret&ouml;&ouml;lepingu s&otilde;lmimisele eelnev arstlik kontroll, mille kulud kannab isik, kes taotleb meret&ouml;&ouml;lepingu s&otilde;lmimist. </eesti>
<inglise>The costs of medical examinations specified in subsections (2) and (3) of this section shall be borne by the shipowner, with the exception of the medical examination conducted prior to entry into a seafarer's contract of employment, the costs of which shall be borne by the person who is seeking to enter into the seafarer's contract of employment. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Eestis registreeritud laeval tagatakse v&auml;ltimatu arstiabi saamiseks tervishoiuasutuse &ouml;&ouml;p&auml;evaringse riigikeelse raadiokonsultatsiooni v&otilde;imalus. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) The opportunity shall be provided for ships registered in Estonia to have a medical consultation by radio in the official language of Estonia with a health care institution twenty-four hours a day in order for emergency care to be provided. </inglise>
<eesti>Tervishoiuasutuse raadiokonsultatsioonikeskuse asutab sotsiaalminister. </eesti>
<inglise>The radio consultation centre of a health care institution shall be established by the Minister of Social Affairs. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Reeder tagab t&ouml;&ouml;tingimused, mis ei kahjusta laevapere liikme elu ja tervist, l&auml;htudes t&ouml;&ouml;tervishoiu ja t&ouml;&ouml;ohutuse seadusega (RT I 1999, 60, 616; 2000, 55, 362; 2001, 17, 78) kehtestatud n&otilde;uetest. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) The shipowner shall ensure working conditions which do not endanger the life or damage the health of crew members, based on the requirements established by the Occupational Health and Safety Act (RT I 1999, 60, 616; 2000, 55, 362; 2001, 17, 78). </inglise>
<eesti>(7) Laevapere liikme t&ouml;&ouml;tervishoiu- ja t&ouml;&ouml;ohutusalast v&auml;lja&otilde;pet korraldab reeder. </eesti>
<inglise>(7) The training of crew members regarding occupational health and safety shall be organised by the shipowner. </inglise>
<eesti>Kapten korraldab laevapere liikme t&ouml;&ouml;tervishoiu- ja t&ouml;&ouml;ohutusalast juhendamist laeval. </eesti>
<inglise>The master shall organise the instruction of crew members regarding occupational health and safety on board the ship. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 29. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 29. </inglise>
<eesti>Haigele v&otilde;i vigastatud laevapere liikmele arstiabi andmine </eesti>
<inglise>Provision of health care to sick or injured crew members </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Reeder v&otilde;i kapten korraldab merereisi ajal haigestunud v&otilde;i vigastatud laevapere liikmele meditsiiniabi andmist ja laevapere liikme ravi laeval v&otilde;i maal. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The shipowner or master shall organise the provision of medical care for a crew member who becomes sick or is injured during the voyage and the treatment of the crew member on the ship or on shore. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Laevapere liikmele merereisi ajal meditsiiniabi osutamisega seotud kulud ja laevapere liikme vajalikud ravikulud kannab reeder. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Expenses related to the provision of medical care for a crew member during a voyage and the costs of the medical treatment necessary for the crew member shall be borne by the shipowner. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 30. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 30. </inglise>
<eesti>Haige v&otilde;i vigastatud laevapere liikme tervishoiuasutusse saatmine </eesti>
<inglise>Sending sick or injured crew member to health care institution </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kui laevapere liikme haigus v&otilde;i vigastus ei v&otilde;imalda tema ravimist laeval v&otilde;i kui laevapere liikme haigus on ohtlik tema v&otilde;i teiste laeval olevate isikute elule v&otilde;i tervisele v&otilde;i kui ei ole v&otilde;imalik v&otilde;tta tarvitusele abin&otilde;usid haiguse leviku v&auml;ltimiseks, saadab kapten laevapere liikme tervishoiuasutusse. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) If the illness or injury of a crew member prevents the crew member from being treated on the ship or if the illness of a crew member is putting his or her life or health or the life or health of other persons on the ship in danger or if it is not possible to take measures to prevent the disease from spreading, the master shall send the crew member to a health care institution. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui haige v&otilde;i vigastatud laevapere liige j&auml;etakse ravile v&auml;lisriiki, korraldab kapten temale arstiabi andmise vastavas tervishoiuasutuses ja teatab sellest reederile. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If a sick or injured crew member is left to be treated in a foreign country, the master shall organise the provision of medical care for the crew member in a suitable health care institution and notify the shipowner thereof. </inglise>
<eesti>Kapten teatab laevapere liikme haigusest v&otilde;i vigastusest laevapere liikme nimetatud isikule. </eesti>
<inglise>The master shall give notice of the illness or injury of a crew member to the person designated by the crew member. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kui haige v&otilde;i vigastatud laevapere liige ei saa hoolitseda laeval oleva oma vara eest, korraldab kapten vara s&auml;ilimise. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) If a sick or injured crew member is not able to attend to his or her property on the ship, the master shall organise the preservation of such property. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) K&auml;esolevas seaduses s&auml;testatud reederi v&otilde;i kapteni kohustus korraldada haigele v&otilde;i vigastatud laevapere liikmele arsti- ja meditsiiniabi andmist l&otilde;peb, kui laevapere liige lahkub laevalt Eesti Vabariigi territooriumil. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The duty of the shipowner or master, provided for in this Act, to organise the provision of health and medical care for a sick or injured crew member terminates if the crew member leaves the ship in the territory of the Republic of Estonia. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Kui laevapere liige on j&auml;etud ravile v&auml;lisriigis, l&otilde;peb reederi v&otilde;i kapteni kohustus korraldada talle arsti- ja meditsiiniabi andmist, kui laevapere liige on j&otilde;udnud Eesti Vabariigi territooriumile. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) If a crew member is left to be treated in a foreign country, the duty of the shipowner or master to organise the provision of health and medical care for the crew member terminates when the crew member arrives in the territory of the Republic of Estonia. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Kui laevapere liige on j&auml;etud ravile v&auml;lisriigis, l&otilde;peb reederi v&otilde;i kapteni kohustus korraldada talle arsti- ja meditsiiniabi andmist ka juhul, kui laevapere liige on &otilde;igustamatult ravi katkestanud. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) If a crew member is left to be treated in a foreign country, the duty of the shipowner or master to organise the provision of health and medical care for the crew member also terminates if the crew member discontinues treatment without authorisation. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 31. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 31. </inglise>
<eesti>Tagasis&otilde;idukulud haigestumise v&otilde;i vigastuse korral </eesti>
<inglise>Repatriation costs in event of illness or injury </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Haigestumise v&otilde;i vigastuse t&otilde;ttu tervishoiuasutusse saadetud laevapere liikme laevale tagasis&otilde;idu kulud koos kulutustega toidule ja majutusele tagasis&otilde;idu ajal kannab reeder. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The costs of returning a crew member sent to a health care institution due to illness or injury to the ship together with the expenses for food and accommodation during his or her return journey shall be borne by the shipowner. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui haigestumise v&otilde;i vigastuse t&otilde;ttu v&auml;lisriigis ravile j&auml;etud laevapere liige ei saa p&auml;rast ravi l&otilde;ppemist laevale tagasi p&ouml;&ouml;rduda, korraldab reeder tema tagasis&otilde;idu vastavalt k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 57 s&auml;testatule. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If a crew member left for treatment in a foreign country due to illness or injury cannot return to the ship after the end of the treatment, the shipowner shall organise the repatriation of the crew member pursuant to the provisions of &sect; 57 of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 32. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 32. </inglise>
<eesti>Laevapere liikme p&otilde;hjustatud haigus v&otilde;i vigastus </eesti>
<inglise>Illness or injury caused by crew member </inglise>
<eesti>Kui haigus v&otilde;i vigastus tekkis laevapere liikme tahtlikkuse v&otilde;i raske hooletuse tagaj&auml;rjel, samuti juhul, kui laevapere liige on tahtlikult varjanud oma tervislikku seisundit, v&otilde;ib reeder n&otilde;uda laevapere liikmelt enda kantud, k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-des 29-31 s&auml;testatud kulude h&uuml;vitamist vastavalt k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 19 l&otilde;ikele 1. </eesti>
<inglise>If an illness or injury is caused by a crew member intentionally or as a result of gross negligence on the part of the crew member, or if a crew member has intentionally concealed his or her state of health, the shipowner is entitled, pursuant to subsection 19 (1) of this Act, to claim compensation from the crew member for expenses provided for in &sect;&sect; 29-31 of this Act and borne by the shipowner. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 33. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 33. </inglise>
<eesti>Laeva merek&otilde;lblikkuse kontrollimine </eesti>
<inglise>Verification of seaworthiness of ships </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kui &uuml;le poole laevapere liikmetest n&otilde;uab kaptenilt laeva merek&otilde;lblikkuse kontrollimist v&otilde;i kui seda n&otilde;uab vanemt&uuml;&uuml;rimees v&otilde;i vanemmehaanik nende vastutusel oleva laevaosa v&otilde;i varustuse suhtes, p&ouml;&ouml;rdub kapten merek&otilde;lblikkuse kontrollimiseks Eestis registreeritud laeva &uuml;le riiklikku j&auml;relevalvet teostava asutuse poole. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) If more than one-half of the crew members request the master to verify the seaworthiness of the ship or if the chief mate or chief mechanic make such a request with regard to the part of the ship or the equipment for which they are responsible, the master shall contact the agency exercising state supervision over ships registered in Estonia to verify the seaworthiness of the ship. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui kontrollimise tulemusena selgub, et k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud n&otilde;ue esitati pahauskselt, h&uuml;vitavad n&otilde;ude esitanud laevapere liikmed sellega reederile tekitatud kahju. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If, as a result of the verification, it becomes evident that the request specified in subsection (1) of this section was made in bad faith, the crew members who made the request shall compensate for the damage caused to the shipowner thereby. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 34. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 34. </inglise>
<eesti>Kord laeval </eesti>
<inglise>Order on ship </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Laevapere liikmed ja teised laeval viibivad isikud peavad alluma kapteni &otilde;igusp&auml;rastele korraldustele. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Crew members and other persons on board a ship shall obey the lawful orders of the master. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kapten tagab korra ja julgeoleku laeval ning on seadusega etten&auml;htud juhtudel ja korras &otilde;igustatud v&otilde;tma selleks tarvitusele vajalikke abin&otilde;usid. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The master shall ensure order and security on board the ship and has the right to take measures necessary therefor in the cases and pursuant to the procedure prescribed by law. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Laeva, sellel viibivat isikut v&otilde;i lasti &auml;hvardava ohu korral, samuti laevapere liikme allumatuse v&otilde;i vastuhaku korral v&otilde;i muudel h&auml;dajuhtudel v&otilde;ib kapten ohu t&otilde;rjumiseks kasutada vajalikke sunnivahendeid. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) In the event of danger to the ship, persons on board the ship or cargo and in the event of insubordination or mutiny on the part of a crew member or in other emergency situations, the master may apply any necessary coercive measures so as to avoid the danger. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Sunnivahendite kohaldamine v&otilde;i korda rikkuvalt isikult vabaduse ajutine v&otilde;tmine on lubatud, kui muude sunnivahendite kasutamine ei ole otstarbekas v&otilde;i v&otilde;imalik. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) It is permitted to apply coercive measures or temporarily to deprive the person who violates the order of his or her liberty if it is not practical or possible to use other coercive measures. </inglise>
<eesti>Vabaduse v&otilde;tmist v&otilde;ib kohaldada &uuml;ksnes juhul, kui see on vajalik k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;igetes 2 ja 3 nimetatud kohustuste t&auml;itmiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>Deprivation of liberty may be applied only if it is necessary to perform the duties specified in subsections (2) and (3) of this section. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 35. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 35. </inglise>
<eesti>Isikute laevale toomine </eesti>
<inglise>Bringing persons on board ship </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Laevapere liige ei v&otilde;i ilma kapteni v&otilde;i teda asendava isiku loata tuua laevale k&otilde;rvalisi isikuid. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Crew members shall not bring other persons on board the ship without the permission of the master or the person substituting for the master. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui laev asub sadamas, ei v&otilde;i kapten v&otilde;i teda asendav isik keelduda loa andmisest laevapere liikme perekonnaliikme laevale toomiseks, kui see ei takista t&ouml;&ouml;d laeval. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) While the ship is in port, the master or the person substituting for the master shall not refuse permission for a crew member to bring a family member on board unless it obstructs work on the ship. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 36. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 36. </inglise>
<eesti>Asjade laevale toomine </eesti>
<inglise>Bringing items on board ship </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Laevapere liige v&otilde;ib laevale tuua isiklikuks tarbimiseks v&otilde;i kasutamiseks m&otilde;eldud asju koguses, mis on reisi kestust ja iseloomu arvestades m&otilde;istlik. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Crew members may bring items intended for personal use on board the ship provided that the quantity of such items is reasonable considering the nature and duration of the voyage. </inglise>
<eesti>Laevapere liikmele tagatakse kindel panipaik isiklike asjade hoidmiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>Crew members shall have secure storage rooms for storing their personal belongings. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetamata asju v&otilde;ib laevapere liige laevale tuua kapteni n&otilde;usolekul. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Crew members may bring items not specified in subsection (1) of this section on board the ship with the permission of the master. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Keelatud on laevale tuua asju, mille hoidmine v&otilde;i vedamine laeval on keelatud v&otilde;i mis ohustavad laeva, laeval viibivat isikut v&otilde;i lasti. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) It is prohibited to bring items on board a ship if their storage or carriage on ships is prohibited or if they endanger the ship, persons on board the ship or the cargo. </inglise>
<eesti>Alkoholi v&otilde;i narkootilisi aineid sisaldava ravimi laevale toomine laevapere liikme poolt on lubatud &uuml;ksnes kapteni loal. </eesti>
<inglise>Medicinal products which contain alcohol or narcotic substances may only be brought on board a ship by a crew member with the permission of the master. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Kui asi on laevale toodud k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;igetes 1-3 s&auml;testatut rikkudes, v&otilde;ib kapten selle enda valdusse v&otilde;tta ja hoiustada. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) If an item is brought on board a ship in violation of the provisions of subsections (1) -(3) of this section, the master may take possession of the item and store it. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui asi ohustab laeva, laeval viibivat isikut v&otilde;i lasti v&otilde;i kui asja hoidmine laeval v&otilde;ib kaasa tuua ametiv&otilde;imude sekkumise, v&otilde;ib kapten n&otilde;uda asja k&otilde;rvaldamist laevalt. </eesti>
<inglise>If the item poses a threat to the ship, persons on board the ship or the cargo or if storage of the item on board the ship may result in intervention by the public authorities, the master may request the item to be removed from the ship. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui laevapere liige asja ei k&otilde;rvalda, v&otilde;ib kapten v&otilde;tta tarvitusele meetmed selle k&otilde;rvaldamiseks laevalt v&otilde;i asja h&auml;vitada. </eesti>
<inglise>If the crew member fails to remove the item, the master may take measures to remove the item from the ship or to destroy it. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;igetes 1-3 s&auml;testatut rikkudes laevale toodud asja eest peab laevapere liige maksma reederile tavaliselt selletaolise asja vedamise eest v&otilde;lgnetavat tasu. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) If an item is brought on board a ship in violation of the provisions of subsections (1) -(3) of this section, the crew member shall pay the shipowner the fee usually payable for the carriage of such items. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Kui kaptenil on p&otilde;hjendatud kahtlusi, et laevale on toodud asju k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;igetes 1-3 s&auml;testatut rikkudes, v&otilde;ib ta korraldada laevapere ruumide ja panipaikade l&auml;biotsimise asjassepuutuvate isikute juuresolekul. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) If the master has reason to suspect that items have been brought on board the ship in violation of the provisions of subsections (1) -(3) of this section, the master may organise a search of the rooms and storage rooms used by the crew in the presence of the persons concerned. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 37. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 37. </inglise>
<eesti>Laevapere liikme asjade h&auml;vimine v&otilde;i kahjustumine </eesti>
<inglise>Destruction of or damage to items of crew members </inglise>
<eesti>(1) K&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 36 l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud asjade h&auml;vimise v&otilde;i kahjustumise korral laeva&otilde;nnetuse, laevahuku v&otilde;i reederist tuleneva asjaolu t&otilde;ttu, h&uuml;vitab reeder laevapere liikmele tekkinud kahju kaubandusliku meres&otilde;idu koodeksis (RT 1991, 46-48, 577; RT I 1993, 65, 923; 1995, 54, 882; 1996, 78, 1380; 1997, 77, 1315; 1998, 2, 47; 23, 321; 30, 409; 2000, 35, 221; 2001, 21, 114; 93, 565; 2002, 1, 1) s&auml;testatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) If the items specified in subsection 36 (1) of this Act are destroyed or damaged in the event of a marine casualty or shipwreck or due to circumstances depending on the shipowner, the shipowner shall compensate the crew member for the damage pursuant to the procedure provided for in the Merchant Shipping Code (RT 1991, 46-48, 577; RT I 1993, 65, 923; 1995, 54, 882; 1996, 78, 1380; 1997, 77, 1315; 1998, 2, 47; 23, 321; 30, 409; 2000, 35, 221; 2001, 21, 114; 93, 565; 2002, 1, 1). </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Muude asjade h&auml;vimise v&otilde;i kahjustumise korral h&uuml;vitatakse kahju laevapere liikmele vastavalt poolte kokkuleppele. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) In the event that other items are destroyed or damaged, the damage shall be compensated to the crew member as agreed by the parties. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 38. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 38. </inglise>
<eesti>Reederi ja kapteni kohustused laevapere liikme surma korral </eesti>
<inglise>Duties of shipowner and master in event of death of crew member </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kui laevapere liige sureb laeval v&otilde;i v&auml;ljaspool Eesti Vabariigi territooriumi laeval t&ouml;&ouml;tamise ajal v&otilde;i ajal, kui reeder v&otilde;i kapten on kohustatud korraldama haigele v&otilde;i vigastatud laevapere liikmele arstiabi andmist, v&otilde;i ajal, kui laevapere liige s&otilde;idab reederi kulul t&ouml;&ouml;tamiskohta v&otilde;i tagasi, teatab reeder v&otilde;i kapten laevapere liikme surmast tema perekonnaliikmele ja korraldab surnukeha toimetamise Eesti Vabariigi territooriumile. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) If a crew member dies on board the ship or outside the territory of the Republic of Estonia while working on the ship or during the time when the shipowner or master is required to organise the provision of health care for the sick or injured crew member or during the time when the crew member is travelling at the expense of the shipowner to the workplace or returning therefrom, the shipowner or master shall notify a family member of the crew member of the death of the crew member and organise repatriation of the body to the territory of the Republic of Estonia. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui surnukeha ei ole v&otilde;imalik toimetada Eesti Vabariigi territooriumile, v&otilde;ib surnu perekonnaliikme n&otilde;usolekul korraldada surnukeha tuhastamise. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If it is not possible to repatriate the body to the territory of the Republic of Estonia, the body may be cremated with the permission of a family member of the deceased. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kui surnukeha ei ole v&otilde;imalik hoida laeval kuni laeva v&auml;lisriigi sadamasse sisenemiseni v&otilde;i see ohustab laeval viibivate isikute tervist v&otilde;i elu- ja t&ouml;&ouml;keskkonda, v&otilde;ib surnukeha matta merel. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) If it is not possible to store a body on the ship until the ship enters a foreign port or if the body poses a threat to the health or the living and working environment of persons on board the ship, the body may be buried at sea. </inglise>
<eesti>Matmise merel v&otilde;ib korraldada ka surnud laevapere liikme perekonnaliikme taotlusel. </eesti>
<inglise>A burial at sea may also be organised at the request of a family member of the deceased crew member. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Matmine merel on keelatud, kui tegemist on kuriteo ohvriga v&otilde;i kui surma p&otilde;hjus on teadmata. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Burial at sea is not permitted if the deceased was a victim of a crime or if the cause of death is unknown. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Surnud laevapere liikme vara hoidmise korraldab ja vara s&auml;ilimise eest vastutab kapten. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) Storage of the property of a deceased crew member shall be organised by the master and the master shall be liable for the preservation of such property. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 39. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 39. </inglise>
<eesti>Laevapere liikme surmaga kaasnevate kulude kandmine </eesti>
<inglise>Bearing of costs related to death of crew member </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Reeder kannab laevapere liikme surnukeha Eesti Vabariigi territooriumile toimetamise kulud. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The costs of repatriating the body of a crew member to the territory of the Republic of Estonia shall be borne by the shipowner. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui laevapere liikme surnukeha ei tooda Eesti Vabariigi territooriumile v&otilde;i kui laevapere liige suri t&ouml;&ouml;kohustuste t&auml;itmisel, kannab reeder laevapere liikme matmise v&otilde;i surnukeha tuhastamise kulud. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If the body of a crew member is not repatriated to the territory of the Republic of Estonia or if the crew member died while performing his or her duties, the shipowner shall bear the costs of the funeral of the crew member or of cremation of the body. </inglise>
<eesti>5. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 5 </inglise>
<eesti>Puhkusega seonduvad erisused </eesti>
<inglise>Specifications Relating to Holidays </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 40. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 40. </inglise>
<eesti>Laevapere liikme puhkus </eesti>
<inglise>Holidays of crew members </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Laevapere liikmel on &otilde;igus iga-aastasele tasustatud p&otilde;hipuhkusele kestusega 28 p&auml;eva v&otilde;i vastavalt t&ouml;&ouml;tatud ajale, kui on t&ouml;&ouml;tatud alla &uuml;he aasta. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A crew member is entitled to an annual paid holiday of a duration of twenty-eight days or corresponding to the time worked if such time is less than one year. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Iga-aastast tasustatud p&otilde;hipuhkust ei v&otilde;i h&uuml;vitada rahas, v&auml;lja arvatud t&ouml;&ouml;suhte l&otilde;petamisel. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The annual paid holiday shall not be compensated for in money, except upon termination of the employment relationship. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 41. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 41. </inglise>
<eesti>Puhkuse andmise koht </eesti>
<inglise>Place of granting holidays </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Puhkus tuleb laevapere liikmele anda Eesti Vabariigi territooriumil, kui pooled ei ole kokku leppinud teisiti. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Crew members shall be granted holidays in the territory of the Republic of Estonia unless otherwise agreed by the parties. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Puhkuse andmisel peab reeder korraldama laevapere liikme kojus&otilde;idu k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 57 s&auml;testatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) When granting a holiday, the shipowner shall organise the return of the crew member to his or her residence pursuant to the procedure provided for in &sect; 57 of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Puhkuse kestuse aja hulka ei arvata laevapere liikme kojus&otilde;idu ja laevale tagasis&otilde;idu aega. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The time for a crew member to travel home and to return to the ship shall not be included in the duration of the holiday. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;igetes 2 ja 3 s&auml;testatut kohaldatakse juhul, kui laev, millel laevapere liige peab p&auml;rast puhkuse l&otilde;ppemist t&ouml;&ouml;le asuma, asub v&auml;ljaspool Eesti Vabariigi territooriumi. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The provisions of subsections (2) and (3) of this section apply if the ship on which the crew member is required to commence work after the end of the holiday is located outside the territory of the Republic of Estonia. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 42. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 42. </inglise>
<eesti>Laevapere liikme &otilde;igus puhkusele p&auml;rast kuuekuulist katkestuseta t&ouml;&ouml;tamist </eesti>
<inglise>Crew member's right to holiday after six months of continuous work </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Laevapere liikmel on p&auml;rast kuuekuulist katkestuseta t&ouml;&ouml;tamist samal laeval v&otilde;i sama reederi laeval &otilde;igus puhkusele. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) After having worked continuously on the same ship or on ships belonging to the same shipowner for six months, a crew member is entitled to a holiday. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Laevapere liige peab k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud juhul puhkuse soovist kaptenile teatama kaks n&auml;dalat ette. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) In the case specified in subsection (1) of this section, the crew member shall notify the master of his or her request for a holiday two weeks in advance. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Puhkuse andmise kohustus tekib p&auml;rast k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 2 nimetatud t&auml;htaja m&ouml;&ouml;dumist, kui laev siseneb sadamasse. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The obligation to grant a holiday arises after expiry of the term specified in subsection (2) of this section and when the ship enters a port. </inglise>
<eesti>Puhkuse andmise kohustust ei teki sadamas, kuhu laev siseneb punkerdamiseks, haige v&otilde;i vigastatud isiku kaldale viimiseks v&otilde;i m&otilde;ne muu etten&auml;gematu s&uuml;ndmuse t&otilde;ttu ja kust laevapere liikme kojusaatmine ei ole m&otilde;istlikult korraldatav. </eesti>
<inglise>The obligation to grant a holiday does not arise in a port which the ship enters for bunkering, to set a sick or injured person ashore or due to any other unforeseeable circumstances and from where the return of the crew member to his or her residence cannot reasonably be organised. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Laevapere liige j&auml;tkab p&auml;rast talle puhkuse andmise kohustuse tekkimist t&ouml;&ouml;d maksimaalselt &uuml;he kuu jooksul, kui talle ei leita vajalikku asendajat v&otilde;i kui on alust arvata, et selle aja jooksul j&otilde;utakse sadamasse, kust laevapere liikme kojus&otilde;itu vastavalt k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 57 s&auml;testatule on lihtsam ja odavam korraldada. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) After the obligation to grant a holiday to a crew member arises, the crew member shall continue work no longer than for one month if a necessary replacement for the crew member cannot be found or if there is reason to believe that during such time the ship will reach a port where from it is easier and cheaper to organise the return of the crew member to his or her residence pursuant to the provisions of &sect; 57 of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>6. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 6 </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;ajaga seonduvad erisused </eesti>
<inglise>Specifications Relating to Working Time </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 43. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 43. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;aja summeeritud arvestuse kohaldamise erisused </eesti>
<inglise>Specifications of application of recording of total working time </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Laevapere liikmele on lubatud kohaldada t&ouml;&ouml;aja summeeritud arvestust kuni kuuekuulise ajavahemiku ulatuses k&auml;esolevast seadusest tulenevate erisustega. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) In the case of crew members, the recording of total working time for periods of time up to six months is permitted, taking account of the specifications arising from this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) T&ouml;&ouml;aja summeeritud arvestuse arvestusperioodi m&auml;&auml;ramisel ei kohaldata t&ouml;&ouml;- ja puhkeaja seaduse (RT I 1994, 2, 12; 1995, 12, 120) &sect; 23 l&otilde;ikes 3 s&auml;testatut. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) When the recording period for the recording of total working time is determined, the provisions of subsection 23 (3) of the Working and Rest Time Act (RT I 1994, 2, 12; 1995, 12, 120) do not apply. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 44. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 44. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;- ja puhkeaja piirangud </eesti>
<inglise>Standard limits on working and rest time </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&ouml;&ouml;aja summeeritud arvestuse kohaldamisel ei v&otilde;i laevapere liikme t&ouml;&ouml;aeg &uuml;letada 12 tundi mis tahes 24-tunnise perioodi jooksul ja 60 tundi mis tahes seitsmep&auml;evase perioodi jooksul tingimusel, et j&auml;rgitakse k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 3, k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 45 l&otilde;ikes 2 ja &sect; 48 l&otilde;ikes 1 s&auml;testatud piiranguid. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Upon the recording of total working time, the working time of a crew member shall not exceed twelve hours in any twenty-four hour period and sixty hours in any period of seven days on the condition that the standard limits provided for in subsection (3) of this section and in subsections 45 (2) and 48 (1) of this Act are observed. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) L&auml;his&otilde;itu sooritaval laeval, mille laevapere liikmete t&ouml;&ouml;ts&uuml;kli pikkus ei &uuml;leta kahte n&auml;dalat, ei v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;aeg &uuml;letada 14 tundi mis tahes 24-tunnise perioodi jooksul ja 72 tundi mis tahes seitsmep&auml;evase perioodi jooksul. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) In the case of a vessel engaged in short sea shipping where the length of the working cycle of the crew members does not exceed two weeks, working time shall not exceed fourteen hours in any twenty-four hour period and seventy-two hours in any period of seven days. </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;letunnit&ouml;&ouml; tegemine k&auml;esolevas l&otilde;ikes s&auml;testatud piirnorme &uuml;letavalt on keelatud. </eesti>
<inglise>It is prohibited to work overtime exceeding the limits provided for in this subsection. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Laevapere liikme puhkeaja mis tahes 24-tunnise perioodi jooksul v&otilde;ib jagada kaheks osaks, millest &uuml;he pikkus peab olema v&auml;hemalt kuus tundi. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The rest period of crew members within any 24-hour period may be divided into two parts, and the length of one of the parts shall be not less than six hours. </inglise>
<eesti>J&auml;rjestikuste puhkeajaperioodide vaheline ajavahemik ei v&otilde;i &uuml;letada 14 tundi. </eesti>
<inglise>The period of time between consecutive rest periods shall not exceed fourteen hours. </inglise>
<eesti>(12.12.2001 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2003 - RT I 2002, 1, 1) </eesti>
<inglise>(12.12.2001 entered into force 01.01.2003 - RT I 2002, 1, 1) </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Laevapere liikmete suhtes on t&ouml;&ouml;andja asukoha (elukoha) t&ouml;&ouml;inspektori n&otilde;usolekul erandina lubatud rakendada k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 s&auml;testatust pikema t&ouml;&ouml;tundide arvuga t&ouml;&ouml;p&auml;eva. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) As an exception, working days with a greater number of working hours than those provided for in subsection (1) of this section may be applied with respect to crew members with the permission of the labour inspector of the location (residence) of the employer. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 45. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 45. </inglise>
<eesti>Vahiteenistuses osalevate laevapere liikmete t&ouml;&ouml;aja re&zcaron;iim </eesti>
<inglise>Working time regime of crew members on watchkeeping duty </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Vahiteenistuses osalevate laevapere liikmete t&ouml;&ouml;aeg tuleb jagada vahtidesse, kui merereis kestab katkestamatult v&auml;hemalt 12 tundi. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The working time of crew members on watchkeeping duty shall be divided into watches if the voyage is continuous for at least twelve hours. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Vahiteenistuses osalevate laevapere liikmete vahtide vahelise puhkeaja mis tahes 24-tunnise perioodi jooksul v&otilde;ib jagada kaheks osaks, millest &uuml;he pikkus peab olema v&auml;hemalt kuus tundi. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The rest period of crew members on watchkeeping duty between watches within any 24-hour period may be divided into two parts, and the length of one of the parts shall be not less than six hours. </inglise>
<eesti>J&auml;rjestikuste puhkeajaperioodide vaheline ajavahemik ei v&otilde;i &uuml;letada 14 tundi. </eesti>
<inglise>The period of time between consecutive rest periods shall not exceed fourteen hours. </inglise>
<eesti>(12.12.2001 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2003 - RT I 2002, 1, 1) </eesti>
<inglise>(12.12.2001 entered into force 01.01.2003 - RT I 2002, 1, 1) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 46. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 46. </inglise>
<eesti>Vahiteenistuses mitteosalevate laevapere liikmete t&ouml;&ouml;aja re&zcaron;iim </eesti>
<inglise>Working time regime of crew members not on watchkeeping duty </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Vahiteenistuses mitteosalevate laevapere liikmete t&ouml;&ouml;aeg peab olema ajavahemikus kella 6.00-st kuni 20.00-ni laeva aja j&auml;rgi, kui see on t&ouml;&ouml; iseloomu arvestades v&otilde;imalik. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The working time of crew members not on watchkeeping duty shall fall within the hours of 6.00 to 20.00 according to ship time if this is possible taking account of the nature of the work. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Ajavahemikus kella 20.00-st kuni 6.00-ni ning p&uuml;hap&auml;eval v&otilde;i riigip&uuml;hal v&otilde;ib vahiteenistuses mitteosalevaid laevapere liikmeid rakendada t&ouml;&ouml;le &uuml;ksnes edasil&uuml;kkamatute t&ouml;&ouml;de tegemiseks, v&auml;lja arvatud juhul, kui laevapere liikme t&ouml;&ouml; iseloom n&otilde;uab t&ouml;&ouml;tamist vastaval ajal. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) During the hours of 20.00 to 6.00 and on Sundays and public holidays, crew members not on watchkeeping duty may be required to work only to perform urgent work, unless the nature of the work of a crew member requires him or her to work at the corresponding time. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 47. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 47. </inglise>
<eesti>Valveaeg </eesti>
<inglise>On-call time </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Laevapere liikme valveajaks on aeg, millal ta on vastavalt temaga s&otilde;lmitud meret&ouml;&ouml;lepingule kohustatud t&ouml;&ouml;ts&uuml;kli ajal viibima laeval ka oma puhkeajal, olemaks k&auml;ttesaadav etten&auml;gematute ja edasil&uuml;kkamatute t&ouml;&ouml;de tegemiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The on-call time of a crew member is the time during which he or she is required, according to his or her seafarer's contract of employment, to stay on board the ship during his or her rest time in a working cycle so as to be available for performing unforeseeable and urgent work. </inglise>
<eesti>Valveaega ei arvata t&ouml;&ouml;aja hulka. </eesti>
<inglise>On-call time is not included in working time. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Valveaja eest maksab reeder laevapere liikmele lisatasu v&otilde;i h&uuml;vitab valveaja lisapuhkeaja andmisega. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The shipowner shall pay additional remuneration to crew members for on-call time or compensate for on-call time by granting additional rest time. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Valveaja kestus, rakendamise kord ja lisatasu suurus v&otilde;i lisapuhkeaja kestus m&auml;&auml;ratakse meret&ouml;&ouml;- v&otilde;i kollektiivlepinguga. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The duration of on-call time, the procedure for implementation thereof and the amount of additional remuneration or the length of additional rest time shall be determined by a seafarer's contract of employment or a collective agreement. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Laevapere liikme suhtes ei kohaldata t&ouml;&ouml;- ja puhkeaja seaduses s&auml;testatud valveaja piirangut. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The standard limit on on-call time provided for in the Working and Rest Time Act does not apply to crew members. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Kapten v&otilde;i teda asendav isik on kohustatud andma k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud juhul laevapere liikmele loa v&auml;ljaspool t&ouml;&ouml;aega maaleminekuks v&auml;hemalt &uuml;ks kord kuuajalise t&ouml;&ouml;ts&uuml;kli jooksul samadel tingimustel teiste laevapere liikmetega. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) In the case specified in subsection (1) of this section, the master or the person substituting for the master shall grant the crew member permission to go ashore outside working time at least once per one-month working cycle under the same conditions as other crew members. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui t&ouml;&ouml;ts&uuml;kli pikkus on l&uuml;hem kui &uuml;ks kuu, antakse luba v&auml;hemalt &uuml;ks kord &uuml;he t&ouml;&ouml;ts&uuml;kli jooksul. </eesti>
<inglise>If the length of the working cycle is less than one month, permission shall be granted at least once during each working cycle. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 48. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 48. </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;letunnit&ouml;&ouml; tegemine </eesti>
<inglise>Overtime </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Laevapere liige v&otilde;ib &uuml;letunnit&ouml;&ouml;d teha kuni kuus tundi mis tahes 24-tunnise perioodi jooksul, kusjuures laevapere liikme t&ouml;&ouml;aeg koos &uuml;letunnit&ouml;&ouml;ga ei v&otilde;i &uuml;letada 14 tundi mis tahes 24-tunnise perioodi jooksul ja 72 tundi mis tahes seitsmep&auml;evase perioodi jooksul. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A crew member may work overtime for up to six hours in any twenty-four hour period, although the working time including overtime of a crew member shall not exceed fourteen hours in any twenty-four hour period and seventy-two hours in any period of seven days. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;tajale tuleb tagada k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 44 l&otilde;ikes 3 ja &sect; 45 l&otilde;ikes 2 s&auml;testatud puhkeaeg. </eesti>
<inglise>The worker shall be guaranteed the rest time provided for in subsections 44 (3) and 45 (2) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Laevapere liikme suhtes ei kohaldata t&ouml;&ouml;- ja puhkeaja seaduses s&auml;testatud &uuml;letunnit&ouml;&ouml; piirnorme. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The standard limits on overtime provided for in the Working and Rest Time Act do not apply to crew members. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 49. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 49. </inglise>
<eesti>Laeva ohutusega seotud edasil&uuml;kkamatud t&ouml;&ouml;d </eesti>
<inglise>Urgent work necessary for safety of ship </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kapten v&otilde;ib laevapere liikmelt n&otilde;uda t&ouml;&ouml; tegemist, kui see on seotud laeva, selle pardal olevate isikute v&otilde;i lasti ohutuse tagamisega v&otilde;i eesm&auml;rgiga abistada mereh&auml;das olevaid isikuid v&otilde;i laevu. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The master may require a crew member to perform any work necessary to guarantee the safety of the ship, persons on board or cargo, or for the purpose of giving assistance to other ships or persons in distress at sea. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml; tegemist v&otilde;ib n&otilde;uda seni, kuni on taastunud normaalne olukord. </eesti>
<inglise>The performance of work may be required until the normal situation has been resumed. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-des 44-48 s&auml;testatud piiranguid t&ouml;&ouml;ajale ei kohaldata laeva ohutusega seotud edasil&uuml;kkamatute t&ouml;&ouml;de tegemisel. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The standard limits on working time provided for in &sect;&sect; 44-48 of this Act do not apply to the performance of work necessary for the safety of the ship. </inglise>
<eesti>Nimetatud alusel tehtud t&ouml;&ouml; ei ole &uuml;letunnit&ouml;&ouml;. </eesti>
<inglise>Work performed on such basis is not overtime. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) P&auml;rast k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud t&ouml;&ouml;de l&otilde;petamist peab kapten laevapere liikmele, kes oli t&ouml;&ouml;l graafikuj&auml;rgselt etten&auml;htud puhkeajal, v&otilde;imaldama sama pikkusega puhkeajaperioodi. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) After the completion of work specified in subsection (1) of this section, the master shall provide any crew members who performed the work in a scheduled rest period with a period of rest of the same length. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) K&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 12 l&otilde;ike 1 punktis 2 nimetatud p&auml;&auml;ste- ja tulet&otilde;rjeharjutused tuleb v&otilde;imaluse korral korraldada viisil, mis v&otilde;imalikult v&auml;he segaks laevapere liikme puhkeaja kasutamist. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The lifeboat and fire-fighting drills specified in clause 12 (1) 2) shall, if possible, be conducted in a manner which disturbs the rest time of crew members as little as possible. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 50. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 50. </inglise>
<eesti>&Otilde;htuse ja &ouml;&ouml;t&ouml;&ouml; h&uuml;vitamise erisused </eesti>
<inglise>Specifications of compensation for evening and night work </inglise>
<eesti>Laevapere liikme suhtes ei kohaldata palgaseaduses (RT I 1994, 11, 154; 1995, 12, 120; 1999, 29, 397; 2000, 10, 59; 40, 248; 2001, 42, 233; 50, 287) s&auml;testatud lisatasu maksmist &otilde;htuse ja &ouml;&ouml;t&ouml;&ouml; eest. </eesti>
<inglise>The payment of additional remuneration for evening and night work provided for in the Wages Act (RT I 1994, 11, 154; 1995, 12, 120; 1999, 29, 397; 2000, 10, 59; 40, 248; 2001, 42, 233; 50, 287) does not apply to crew members. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 51. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 51. </inglise>
<eesti>Arvestuse pidamine laevapere liikme t&ouml;&ouml;- ja puhkeaja kohta </eesti>
<inglise>Keeping of records on working and rest time of crew members </inglise>
<eesti>Kapten peab laevapere liikme t&ouml;&ouml;- ja puhkeaja arvestust. </eesti>
<inglise>The master shall keep records on the working and rest time of crew members. </inglise>
<eesti>Laevapere liikmel on &otilde;igus saada arvestuse koopia. </eesti>
<inglise>Each crew member is entitled to have a copy of such records. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;- ja puhkeaja arvestuse pidamise korra ja vormi kehtestab sotsiaalminister. </eesti>
<inglise>The procedure for and format of keeping records on working and rest time shall be established by the Minister of Social Affairs. </inglise>
<eesti>7. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 7 </inglise>
<eesti>Distsiplinaarkaristuse m&auml;&auml;ramisega seonduvad erisused </eesti>
<inglise>Specifications Relating to Imposition of Disciplinary Penalties </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 52. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 52. </inglise>
<eesti>Laevapere liikme s&uuml;&uuml;teo arutamise kord merereisi ajal </eesti>
<inglise>Procedure for considering offences of crew members during voyage </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kui laevapere liiget kahtlustatakse merereisi ajal distsiplinaars&uuml;&uuml;teo toimepanemises, arutatakse seda tegu ja langetatakse otsus 14 p&auml;eva jooksul komisjonis, mis koosneb kolmest laevapere liikmest. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) If a crew member is suspected of committing a disciplinary offence during a voyage, the offence shall be considered and a decision shall be made within fourteen days by a committee consisting of three crew members. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Komisjoni esimeheks on kapten. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The master shall be the chairman of the committee. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui teo toimepanemises kahtlustatakse laevapere liiget, kes kuulub laeva juhtkonda, nimetab kapten &uuml;lej&auml;&auml;nud kaks komisjoni liiget laeva juhtkonda kuuluvate isikute hulgast. </eesti>
<inglise>If the crew member who is suspected of committing an offence is a ship's officer, the master shall appoint the two other members of the committee from among the ship's officers. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui teo toimepanemises kahtlustatakse laevapere liiget, kes ei kuulu laeva juhtkonda, nimetab kapten &uuml;he komisjoni liikme laeva juhtkonda kuuluvate isikute hulgast, teise valivad laevapere liikmed. </eesti>
<inglise>If the crew member who is suspected of committing an offence is not a ship's officer, the master shall appoint one of the members of the committee from among the ship's officers and the other member shall be elected by the crew members. </inglise>
<eesti>Komisjoni esimees nimetab laevapere liikmete hulgast protokollija. </eesti>
<inglise>The chairman of the committee shall appoint a secretary from among the crew members. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Teo arutamisel on asjaomasel laevapere liikmel &otilde;igus anda seletusi. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) When an offence is considered, the crew member concerned has the right to provide explanations. </inglise>
<eesti>Komisjoni liikmed v&otilde;ivad esitada k&uuml;simusi nii asjaomasele laevapere liikmele kui ka teistele isikutele, kelle &uuml;tlustel v&otilde;ib teo arutamisel t&auml;htsust olla. </eesti>
<inglise>Members of the committee may ask questions of the crew member concerned and of other persons whose statements may have a bearing upon the consideration of the offence. </inglise>
<eesti>Otsus tehakse h&auml;&auml;lteenamusega. </eesti>
<inglise>Decisions shall be made by majority vote. </inglise>
<eesti>K&uuml;simused, seletused, vastused ja komisjoni p&otilde;hjendatud otsus protokollitakse ning loetakse asjaosalisele ette. </eesti>
<inglise>Questions, explanations, answers and the reasoned decision of the committee shall be recorded in the minutes and read to the persons concerned. </inglise>
<eesti>Protokolli &otilde;igsust kinnitavad komisjoni liikmed oma allkirjaga. </eesti>
<inglise>The members of the committee shall verify the accuracy of the minutes by their signatures. </inglise>
<eesti>Protokollile v&otilde;etakse ka asjaomase laevapere liikme allkiri. </eesti>
<inglise>The minutes shall also be signed by the crew member concerned. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui asjaomane laevapere liige keeldub protokollile alla kirjutamast, teeb protokollija selle kohta protokolli m&auml;rkuse. </eesti>
<inglise>If the crew member concerned refuses to sign the minutes, the secretary shall make a corresponding notation in the report. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 53. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 53. </inglise>
<eesti>Distsiplinaarkaristuse m&auml;&auml;ramine </eesti>
<inglise>Imposition of disciplinary penalties </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kui komisjon tuvastab laevapere liikme s&uuml;&uuml;, m&auml;&auml;ratakse talle distsiplinaarkaristus, informeerides sellest reederit enne kapteni k&auml;skkirja kehtestamist. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) If the committee establishes that the crew member is guilty, a disciplinary penalty shall be imposed on the crew member and the shipowner shall be informed thereof prior to the entry into force of the directive of the master. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui komisjon otsustab, et distsiplinaarkaristusena tuleb kohaldada meret&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamist, edastab kapten komisjoni kogutud materjalid reederile. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If the committee decides the disciplinary penalty will be the termination of the seafarer's contract of employment, the master shall forward the materials collected to the shipowner. </inglise>
<eesti>Reeder peab tegema otsuse kohaldatava distsiplinaarkaristuse kohta 30 p&auml;eva jooksul materjalide k&auml;ttesaamisest arvates, aga mitte hiljem kui kuue kuu jooksul teo toimepanemisest arvates. </eesti>
<inglise>The shipowner shall make a decision concerning the disciplinary penalty imposed within thirty days as of receipt of the materials but not later than during six months as of the commission of the offence. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) P&auml;rast reederi poolt otsuse langetamist toimib kapten reederilt saadud korralduste alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) After the shipowner has made a decision, the master shall act according to orders from the shipowner. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Komisjoni otsusega mitten&otilde;ustumise korral on asjaomasel laevapere liikmel &otilde;igus p&ouml;&ouml;rduda t&ouml;&ouml;vaidluskomisjoni v&otilde;i kohtusse &uuml;he kuu jooksul, arvates p&auml;evast, mis j&auml;rgnes p&auml;evale, millal ta p&ouml;&ouml;rdus tagasi Eesti Vabariigi territooriumile. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) If the crew member concerned disagrees with the decision of the committee, he or she has the right of recourse to a labour dispute committee or a court within one month as of the date following the date on which the crew member returns to the territory of the Republic of Estonia. </inglise>
<eesti>8. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 8 </inglise>
<eesti>Meret&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;ppemisega seonduvad erisused </eesti>
<inglise>Specifications Relating to Termination of Seafarer's Contract of Employment </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 54. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 54. </inglise>
<eesti>Laevapere liikme j&auml;me t&ouml;&ouml;kohustuste rikkumine </eesti>
<inglise>Major breach of duties of employment by crew member </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Laevapere liikme j&auml;medaks t&ouml;&ouml;kohustuste rikkumiseks k&auml;esoleva seaduse t&auml;henduses on: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) For the purposes of this Act, the following are considered major breaches of duties by a crew member: </inglise>
<eesti>1) tahtlik v&otilde;i raskelt hooletu laevale saabumata j&auml;&auml;mine oma t&ouml;&ouml;aja alguseks v&otilde;i laeva v&auml;ljumise ajaks; </eesti>
<inglise>1) intentional failure to arrive on the ship by the beginning of working time or by the time of departure of the ship, or failure to arrive on time due to gross negligence; </inglise>
<eesti>2) omavoliline lahkumine laevalt oma t&ouml;&ouml;ajal; </eesti>
<inglise>2) leaving the ship during working time without permission; </inglise>
<eesti>3) laeval olemine alkohoolses, narkootilises v&otilde;i toksilises joobes; </eesti>
<inglise>3) being on board the ship under the influence of alcohol or narcotic or toxic substances; </inglise>
<eesti>4) narkootiliste v&otilde;i ohtlike ainete laevale toomine; </eesti>
<inglise>4) bringing narcotic or dangerous substances on board the ship; </inglise>
<eesti>5) tegelemine salakaubaveoga; </eesti>
<inglise>5) being engaged in illicit trafficking; </inglise>
<eesti>6) tegevus, mis seab reaalsesse ohtu laeva, laeval viibiva isiku v&otilde;i laeva lasti. </eesti>
<inglise>6) activities which actually endanger the ship or persons or cargo on board the ship. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud alustel on reederil v&otilde;i muul t&ouml;&ouml;andjal &otilde;igus l&otilde;petada meret&ouml;&ouml;leping ette teatamata ja h&uuml;vitist maksmata. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A shipowner or any other employer has the right to terminate a seafarer's contract of employment on the bases specified in subsection (1) of this section without giving prior notice and without paying compensation. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 55. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 55. </inglise>
<eesti>Meret&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;ppemine laeva merek&otilde;lbmatuks muutumise ja laevahuku korral </eesti>
<inglise>Termination of seafarer's contract of employment if ship ceases to be seaworthy and in event of shipwreck </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kui laev muutub merek&otilde;lbmatuks v&otilde;i toimub laevahukk, on reederil &otilde;igus l&otilde;petada meret&ouml;&ouml;leping laevapere liikmega koondamise t&otilde;ttu, kui reederil ei ole v&otilde;imalik pakkuda laevapere liikmele t&ouml;&ouml;d muul laeval oma ettev&otilde;ttes. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) If a ship ceases to be seaworthy or in the event of a shipwreck, the shipowner has the right to terminate the seafarer's contract of employment with a crew member due to redundancy if the shipowner is not able to provide the crew member with work on another ship within the shipowner's enterprise. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Laevahuku korral on reederil &otilde;igus l&otilde;petada meret&ouml;&ouml;leping laevapere liikmele ette teatamata. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) In the event of a shipwreck, the shipowner has the right to terminate the seafarer's contract of employment without giving the crew member prior notice. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Laeva merek&otilde;lbmatuks muutumise korral avarii tagaj&auml;rjel teatab reeder meret&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamisest laevapere liikmele viis p&auml;eva ette. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) If a ship ceases to be seaworthy as a result of an accident, the shipowner shall give notice to the crew member of the termination of his or her seafarer's contract of employment five days in advance. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Laevapere liikmega kindlaksm&auml;&auml;ratud reisiks s&otilde;lmitud meret&ouml;&ouml;leping l&otilde;peb seda reisi tegeva laeva avarii tagaj&auml;rjel merek&otilde;lbmatuks muutumise v&otilde;i laevahuku korral. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) A seafarer's contract of employment entered into with a crew member for a particular voyage shall terminate if the ship making the voyage ceases to be seaworthy as a result of an accident or in the event of a shipwreck. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 56. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 56. </inglise>
<eesti>Meret&ouml;&ouml;lepingu pikenemine </eesti>
<inglise>Extension of seafarer's contract of employment </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kui meret&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;ppemise aeg saabub laeva mereloleku ajal, loetakse leping pikenenuks kuni laeva esimesse sadamasse j&otilde;udmiseni. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) If the time of termination of a seafarer's contract of employment arrives while the ship is at sea, the contract shall be considered to be extended until the ship enters the next port. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Meret&ouml;&ouml;leping ei l&otilde;pe k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud juhtudel sadamas, kuhu laev siseneb ainult punkerdamiseks, haige v&otilde;i vigastatud isiku kaldale viimiseks v&otilde;i m&otilde;ne muu etten&auml;gematu s&uuml;ndmuse t&otilde;ttu ja kui laevapere liikme kojusaatmine ei ole m&otilde;istlikult korraldatav. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) In the cases specified in subsection (1) of this section, a seafarer's contract of employment shall not terminate in a port which the ship enters only for bunkering, to set a sick or injured person ashore or due to any other unforeseeable event and if repatriation of the crew member cannot be reasonably organised. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kui laevapere liige j&auml;tkab t&ouml;&ouml;d p&auml;rast k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud sadamasse j&otilde;udmist reederi v&otilde;i kapteni ettepanekul, loetakse meret&ouml;&ouml;leping pikenenuks m&auml;&auml;ramata ajaks, kui ei ole kokku lepitud teisiti. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) If a crew member continues work on the proposal of the shipowner or master after entry into a port specified in subsection (1) of this section, the seafarer's contract of employment is considered to be extended for an unspecified term unless otherwise agreed. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui t&ouml;&ouml;d j&auml;tkatakse reederi v&otilde;i kapteni n&otilde;udmisel asendaja leidmiseni, kohaldatakse k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 4 s&auml;testatut. </eesti>
<inglise>If work is continued at the request of the shipowner or master until a replacement is found, the provisions of subsection (4) of this section apply. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Laevapere liige peab reederi v&otilde;i kapteni n&otilde;udmisel p&auml;rast k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud sadamasse j&otilde;udmist j&auml;tkama t&ouml;&ouml;tamist kuni n&auml;dal aega, kui laevapere liikme ametikohale ei ole leitud asendajat. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) At the request of the shipowner or master, a crew member shall continue work after the ship enters a port specified in subsection (1) of this section for up to one week if a replacement has not been found for the position of the crew member. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Kui v&auml;lisriigi v&otilde;imud ei luba laevapere liiget maale t&ouml;&ouml;lt lahkumise kohal v&otilde;i n&otilde;uavad tema k&auml;est tagatisi, mida laevapere liige ei saa anda, loetakse meret&ouml;&ouml;leping pikenenuks kuni laeva j&otilde;udmiseni sadamasse, kus ei ole k&auml;esolevas l&otilde;ikes nimetatud takistusi. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) If foreign authorities do not permit a crew member to go ashore at the place he or she is to leave work or request security from the crew member which the crew member is not able to provide, his or her seafarer's contract of employment is considered to be extended until the ship enters a port where there are none of the obstacles specified in this subsection. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 57. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 57. </inglise>
<eesti>Laevapere liikme kojus&otilde;idu korraldamise kohustus </eesti>
<inglise>Duty to organise repatriation of crew members </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Meret&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;ppemisel korraldab reeder oma kulul laevapere liikme s&otilde;idu, eelistatult &otilde;hutransporti kasutades, tema soovil kas: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) When a seafarer's contract of employment terminates, the shipowner shall organise, at the shipowner's expense, the return of the crew member, preferably by air, to the location of the crew member's request from among the following: </inglise>
<eesti>1) Eesti Vabariigi territooriumile, </eesti>
<inglise>1) the territory of the Republic of Estonia; </inglise>
<eesti>2) laevapere liikme elukohariiki, </eesti>
<inglise>2) the country of residence of the crew member; </inglise>
<eesti>3) kollektiivlepingus kindlaksm&auml;&auml;ratud kohta, </eesti>
<inglise>3) a place determined in a collective agreement; </inglise>
<eesti>4) laeva v&auml;ljas&otilde;idu sadamasse, </eesti>
<inglise>4) the port of departure of the ship; </inglise>
<eesti>5) meret&ouml;&ouml;lepingu s&otilde;lmimise kohta v&otilde;i </eesti>
<inglise>5) the place where the seafarer's contract of employment was concluded, or </inglise>
<eesti>6) kohta, milles lepiti kokku meret&ouml;&ouml;lepingu s&otilde;lmimisel. </eesti>
<inglise>6) the place agreed on upon entry into the seafarer's contract of employment. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Reeder kannab laevapere liikme toidu- ja majutuskulud alates tema lahkumisest laevalt kuni saabumiseni sihtkohta ning laevapere liikme kuni 20 kg raskuse pagasi sihtkohta transportimise kulud. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The shipowner shall bear the food and accommodation expenses of the crew member from when the crew member leaves the ship until he or she arrives at his or her destination and the costs of transporting up to 20 kg of luggage of the crew member to his or her destination. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 s&auml;testatud reederi kohustused loetakse t&auml;idetuks ka siis, kui laevapere liige on keeldunud temale vastavalt l&otilde;ikele 1 korraldatavast s&otilde;idust. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The duties of the shipowner as provided for in subsection (1) of this section shall be deemed to have been fulfilled if the crew member has refused the journey organised for him or her pursuant to subsection (1). </inglise>
<eesti>(4) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 s&auml;testatud reederi kohustused ei ole t&auml;idetud, kui laevapere liiget ei lubata l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud riigi territooriumile v&otilde;i n&otilde;utakse selleks tagatisi, mida laevapere liige ei ole suuteline andma. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The duties of the shipowner as provided for in subsection (1) of this section are not deemed to have been fulfilled if the crew member is not permitted into the territory of the country specified in subsection (1) or security is required therefor which the crew member is not able to provide. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Kui laevapere liikmega s&otilde;lmitud meret&ouml;&ouml;leping l&otilde;petati laevapere liikme t&ouml;&ouml;kohustuste rikkumise, laevapere liikme suhtes usalduse kaotamise v&otilde;i laevapere liikme haiguse v&otilde;i vigastuse t&otilde;ttu, mida ta meret&ouml;&ouml;lepingu s&otilde;lmimisel varjas v&otilde;i mille ta iseendale tahtlikult tekitas, v&otilde;ib reeder n&otilde;uda temalt vastavalt k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikele 2 kantud kulude h&uuml;vitamist ja vajaliku asendaja laevale toimetamiseks kantud kulude h&uuml;vitamist k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 19 s&auml;testatud alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) If a seafarer's contract of employment entered into with a crew member is terminated due to a breach of duties by the crew member, loss of confidence in the crew member or illness of or injury to the crew member which the crew member concealed upon entering into the seafarer's contract of employment or which the crew member intentionally inflicted upon himself or herself, the shipowner is entitled to claim compensation, on the basis provided for in &sect; 19 of this Act, from the crew member for expenses borne pursuant to subsection (2) of this section and expenses borne to transport the necessary replacement to the ship. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Laevapere liikme, kes on v&auml;lisriigi sadamas mitte oma s&uuml;&uuml; t&otilde;ttu laevalt maha j&auml;&auml;nud, toimetab reeder oma kulul Eesti Vabariigi territooriumile v&otilde;i j&auml;rgmisesse sadamasse, kuhu laev siirdub. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) The shipowner shall, at the shipowner's expense, transport a crew member who misses the ship in a foreign port due to no fault of the crew member to the territory of the Republic of Estonia or to the next port to which the ship is proceeding. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 58. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 58. </inglise>
<eesti>Meret&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;ppemise aeg </eesti>
<inglise>Time of termination of seafarer's contract of employment </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Meret&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;ppemise p&auml;evaks on p&auml;ev, millal laevapere liige j&otilde;uab k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 57 l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud kohta. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The date of termination of a seafarer's contract of employment shall be the date on which the crew member arrives at the place specified in subsection 57 (1) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui laevapere liige keeldub temale vastavalt k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 57 l&otilde;ikele 1 v&otilde;imaldatavast s&otilde;idust, loetakse meret&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;ppemise p&auml;evaks laevapere liikme t&ouml;&ouml;loleku viimane p&auml;ev. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If a crew member refuses a journey provided for him or her pursuant to subsection 57 (1) of this Act, the date of termination of his or her seafarer's contract of employment shall be his or her last working day. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kui laevapere liikmega s&otilde;lmitud meret&ouml;&ouml;leping l&otilde;petati laevapere liikme algatusel v&otilde;i laevapere liikme t&ouml;&ouml;kohustuste rikkumise, laevapere liikme suhtes usalduse kaotamise v&otilde;i laevapere liikme haiguse v&otilde;i vigastuse t&otilde;ttu, mida ta meret&ouml;&ouml;lepingu s&otilde;lmimisel varjas v&otilde;i mille ta iseendale tahtlikult tekitas, loetakse meret&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;ppemise p&auml;evaks laevapere liikme t&ouml;&ouml;loleku viimane p&auml;ev. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) If a seafarer's contract of employment is terminated on the initiative of the crew member or due to a breach of duties by the crew member, loss of confidence in the crew member or illness of or injury to the crew member which the crew member concealed upon entering into the seafarer's contract of employment or which the crew member intentionally inflicted upon himself or herself, the date of termination of his or her seafarer's contract of employment shall be his or her last working day. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 59. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 59. </inglise>
<eesti>Meret&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamine laevapere liikme algatusel </eesti>
<inglise>Termination of seafarer's contract of employment on initiative of crew member </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Laevapere liige v&otilde;ib l&otilde;petada meret&ouml;&ouml;lepingu, kui reeder rikub meret&ouml;&ouml;lepingut ning lepingu rikkumise p&otilde;hjusteks on k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 18 l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud asjaolud. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A crew member may terminate his or her seafarer's contract of employment if the shipowner violates the seafarer's contract of employment and if the reasons for violation of the contract are the circumstances specified in subsection 18 (1) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>Laevapere liige peab meret&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamisest teatama viis p&auml;eva ette. </eesti>
<inglise>The crew member shall give notice of the termination of his or her seafarer's contract of employment five days in advance. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui meret&ouml;&ouml;leping l&otilde;petatakse k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 s&auml;testatud alustel, maksab reeder laevapere liikmele h&uuml;vitist kahe keskmise kuupalga ulatuses. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If a seafarer's contract of employment is terminated on the bases provided for in subsection (1) of this section, the shipowner shall pay the crew member compensation to the extent of twice the average monthly wages. </inglise>
